65struct dns_dispatchmgr {
66 /* Unlocked. */
67 unsigned int magic;
68 isc_mem_t *mctx;
69 dns_acl_t *blackhole;
70 dns_portlist_t *portlist;
71 isc_stats_t *stats;
72
73 /* Locked by "lock". */
74 isc_mutex_t lock;
75 unsigned int state;
76 ISC_LIST(dns_dispatch_t) list;
77
78 /* locked by buffer_lock */
79 dns_qid_t *qid;
80 isc_mutex_t buffer_lock;
81 unsigned int buffers; /*%< allocated buffers */
82 unsigned int buffersize; /*%< size of each buffer */
83 unsigned int maxbuffers; /*%< max buffers */
84
85 /* Locked internally. */
86 isc_mutex_t depool_lock;
87 isc_mempool_t *depool; /*%< pool for dispatch events */
88 isc_mutex_t rpool_lock;
89 isc_mempool_t *rpool; /*%< pool for replies */
90 isc_mutex_t dpool_lock;
91 isc_mempool_t *dpool; /*%< dispatch allocations */
92 isc_mutex_t bpool_lock;
93 isc_mempool_t *bpool; /*%< pool for buffers */
94 isc_mutex_t spool_lock;
95 isc_mempool_t *spool; /*%< pool for dispsocks */
96
97 /*%
98 * Locked by qid->lock if qid exists; otherwise, can be used without
99 * being locked.
100 * Memory footprint considerations: this is a simple implementation of
101 * available ports, i.e., an ordered array of the actual port numbers.
102 * This will require about 256KB of memory in the worst case (128KB for
103 * each of IPv4 and IPv6). We could reduce it by representing it as a
104 * more sophisticated way such as a list (or array) of ranges that are
105 * searched to identify a specific port. Our decision here is the saved
106 * memory isn't worth the implementation complexity, considering the
107 * fact that the whole BIND9 process (which is mainly named) already
108 * requires a pretty large memory footprint. We may, however, have to
109 * revisit the decision when we want to use it as a separate module for
110 * an environment where memory requirement is severer.
111 */
112 in_port_t *v4ports; /*%< available ports for IPv4 */
113 unsigned int nv4ports; /*%< # of available ports for IPv4 */
114 in_port_t *v6ports; /*%< available ports for IPv4 */
115 unsigned int nv6ports; /*%< # of available ports for IPv4 */
116};

139/*%
140 * Maximum number of dispatch sockets that can be pooled for reuse. The
141 * appropriate value may vary, but experiments have shown a busy caching server
142 * may need more than 1000 sockets concurrently opened. The maximum allowable
143 * number of dispatch sockets (per manager) will be set to the double of this
144 * value.
145 */
146#ifndef DNS_DISPATCH_POOLSOCKS
147#define DNS_DISPATCH_POOLSOCKS 2048
148#endif
149
150/*%
151 * Quota to control the number of dispatch sockets. If a dispatch has more
152 * than the quota of sockets, new queries will purge oldest ones, so that
153 * a massive number of outstanding queries won't prevent subsequent queries
154 * (especially if the older ones take longer time and result in timeout).
155 */
156#ifndef DNS_DISPATCH_SOCKSQUOTA
157#define DNS_DISPATCH_SOCKSQUOTA 3072
158#endif

174/*%
175 * A port table entry. We remember every port we first open in a table with a
176 * reference counter so that we can 'reuse' the same port (with different
177 * destination addresses) using the SO_REUSEADDR socket option.
178 */
179struct dispportentry {
180 in_port_t port;
181 unsigned int refs;
182 ISC_LINK(struct dispportentry) link;
183};

191/*%
192 * Number of tasks for each dispatch that use separate sockets for different
193 * transactions. This must be a power of 2 as it will divide 32 bit numbers
194 * to get an uniformly random tasks selection. See get_dispsocket().
195 */
196#define MAX_INTERNAL_TASKS 64

198struct dns_dispatch {
199 /* Unlocked. */
200 unsigned int magic; /*%< magic */
201 dns_dispatchmgr_t *mgr; /*%< dispatch manager */
202 int ntasks;
203 /*%
204 * internal task buckets. We use multiple tasks to distribute various
205 * socket events well when using separate dispatch sockets. We use the
206 * 1st task (task[0]) for internal control events.
207 */
208 isc_task_t *task[MAX_INTERNAL_TASKS];
209 isc_socket_t *socket; /*%< isc socket attached to */
210 isc_sockaddr_t local; /*%< local address */
211 in_port_t localport; /*%< local UDP port */
212 isc_sockaddr_t peer; /*%< peer address (TCP) */
213 isc_dscp_t dscp; /*%< "listen-on" DSCP value */
214 unsigned int maxrequests; /*%< max requests */
215 isc_event_t *ctlevent;
216
217 isc_mutex_t sepool_lock;
218 isc_mempool_t *sepool; /*%< pool for socket events */
219
220 /*% Locked by mgr->lock. */
221 ISC_LINK(dns_dispatch_t) link;
222
223 /* Locked by "lock". */
224 isc_mutex_t lock; /*%< locks all below */
225 isc_sockettype_t socktype;
226 unsigned int attributes;
227 unsigned int refcount; /*%< number of users */
228 dns_dispatchevent_t *failsafe_ev; /*%< failsafe cancel event */
229 unsigned int shutting_down : 1,
230 shutdown_out : 1,
231 connected : 1,
232 tcpmsg_valid : 1,
233 recv_pending : 1; /*%< is a recv() pending? */
234 isc_result_t shutdown_why;
235 ISC_LIST(dispsocket_t) activesockets;
236 ISC_LIST(dispsocket_t) inactivesockets;
237 unsigned int nsockets;
238 unsigned int requests; /*%< how many requests we have */
239 unsigned int tcpbuffers; /*%< allocated buffers */
240 dns_tcpmsg_t tcpmsg; /*%< for tcp streams */
241 dns_qid_t *qid;
242 dispportlist_t *port_table; /*%< hold ports 'owned' by us */
243 isc_mempool_t *portpool; /*%< port table entries */
244};

264/*%
265 * Locking a query port buffer is a bit tricky. We access the buffer without
266 * locking until qid is created. Technically, there is a possibility of race
267 * between the creation of qid and access to the port buffer; in practice,
268 * however, this should be safe because qid isn't created until the first
269 * dispatch is created and there should be no contending situation until then.
270 */
271#define PORTBUFLOCK(mgr) if ((mgr)->qid != NULL) LOCK(&((mgr)->qid->lock))
272#define PORTBUFUNLOCK(mgr) if ((mgr)->qid != NULL) UNLOCK((&(mgr)->qid->lock))

333static void
334mgr_log(dns_dispatchmgr_t *mgr, int level, const char *fmt, ...) {
335 char msgbuf[2048];
336 va_list ap;
337
338 if (! isc_log_wouldlog(dns_lctx, level))
339 return;
340
341 va_start(ap, fmt);
342 vsnprintf(msgbuf, sizeof(msgbuf), fmt, ap);
343 va_end(ap);
344
345 isc_log_write(dns_lctx,
346 DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DISPATCH, DNS_LOGMODULE_DISPATCH,
347 level, "dispatchmgr %p: %s", mgr, msgbuf);
348}

383static void
384request_log(dns_dispatch_t *disp, dns_dispentry_t *resp,
385 int level, const char *fmt, ...)
386 ISC_FORMAT_PRINTF(4, 5);
387
388static void
389request_log(dns_dispatch_t *disp, dns_dispentry_t *resp,
390 int level, const char *fmt, ...)
391{
392 char msgbuf[2048];
393 char peerbuf[256];
394 va_list ap;
395
396 if (! isc_log_wouldlog(dns_lctx, level))
397 return;
398
399 va_start(ap, fmt);
400 vsnprintf(msgbuf, sizeof(msgbuf), fmt, ap);
401 va_end(ap);
402
403 if (VALID_RESPONSE(resp)) {
404 isc_sockaddr_format(&resp->host, peerbuf, sizeof(peerbuf));
405 isc_log_write(dns_lctx, DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DISPATCH,
406 DNS_LOGMODULE_DISPATCH, level,
407 "dispatch %p response %p %s: %s", disp, resp,
408 peerbuf, msgbuf);
409 } else {
410 isc_log_write(dns_lctx, DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DISPATCH,
411 DNS_LOGMODULE_DISPATCH, level,
412 "dispatch %p req/resp %p: %s", disp, resp,
413 msgbuf);
414 }
415}

417/*
418 * Return a hash of the destination and message id.
419 */
420static uint32_t
421dns_hash(dns_qid_t *qid, const isc_sockaddr_t *dest, dns_messageid_t id,
422 in_port_t port)
423{
424 uint32_t ret;
425
426 ret = isc_sockaddr_hash(dest, true);
427 ret ^= ((uint32_t)id << 16) | port;
428 ret %= qid->qid_nbuckets;
429
430 INSIST(ret < qid->qid_nbuckets);
431
432 return (ret);
433}

435/*
436 * Find the first entry in 'qid'. Returns NULL if there are no entries.
437 */
438static dns_dispentry_t *
439linear_first(dns_qid_t *qid) {
440 dns_dispentry_t *ret;
441 unsigned int bucket;
442
443 bucket = 0;
444
445 while (bucket < qid->qid_nbuckets) {
446 ret = ISC_LIST_HEAD(qid->qid_table[bucket]);
447 if (ret != NULL)
448 return (ret);
449 bucket++;
450 }
451
452 return (NULL);
453}
454
455/*
456 * Find the next entry after 'resp' in 'qid'. Return NULL if there are
457 * no more entries.
458 */
459static dns_dispentry_t *
460linear_next(dns_qid_t *qid, dns_dispentry_t *resp) {
461 dns_dispentry_t *ret;
462 unsigned int bucket;
463
464 ret = ISC_LIST_NEXT(resp, link);
465 if (ret != NULL)
466 return (ret);
467
468 bucket = resp->bucket;
469 bucket++;
470 while (bucket < qid->qid_nbuckets) {
471 ret = ISC_LIST_HEAD(qid->qid_table[bucket]);
472 if (ret != NULL)
473 return (ret);
474 bucket++;
475 }
476
477 return (NULL);
478}

480/*
481 * The dispatch must be locked.
482 */
483static bool
484destroy_disp_ok(dns_dispatch_t *disp)
485{
486 if (disp->refcount != 0)
487 return (false);
488
489 if (disp->recv_pending != 0)
490 return (false);
491
492 if (!ISC_LIST_EMPTY(disp->activesockets))
493 return (false);
494
495 if (disp->shutting_down == 0)
496 return (false);
497
498 return (true);
499}
500
501/*
502 * Called when refcount reaches 0 (and safe to destroy).
503 *
504 * The dispatcher must be locked.
505 * The manager must not be locked.
506 */
507static void
508destroy_disp(isc_task_t *task, isc_event_t *event) {
509 dns_dispatch_t *disp;
510 dns_dispatchmgr_t *mgr;
511 bool killmgr;
512 dispsocket_t *dispsocket;
513 int i;
514
515 INSIST(event->ev_type == DNS_EVENT_DISPATCHCONTROL);
516
517 UNUSED(task);
518
519 disp = event->ev_arg;
520 mgr = disp->mgr;
521
522 LOCK(&mgr->lock);
523 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(mgr->list, disp, link);
524
525 dispatch_log(disp, LVL(90),
526 "shutting down; detaching from sock %p, task %p",
527 disp->socket, disp->task[0]); /* XXXX */
528
529 if (disp->sepool != NULL) {
530 isc_mempool_destroy(&disp->sepool);
531 isc_mutex_destroy(&disp->sepool_lock);
532 }
533
534 if (disp->socket != NULL)
535 isc_socket_detach(&disp->socket);
536 while ((dispsocket = ISC_LIST_HEAD(disp->inactivesockets)) != NULL) {
537 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(disp->inactivesockets, dispsocket, link);
538 destroy_dispsocket(disp, &dispsocket);
539 }
540 for (i = 0; i < disp->ntasks; i++)
541 isc_task_detach(&disp->task[i]);
542 isc_event_free(&event);
543
544 dispatch_free(&disp);
545
546 killmgr = destroy_mgr_ok(mgr);
547 UNLOCK(&mgr->lock);
548 if (killmgr)
549 destroy_mgr(&mgr);
550}

552/*%
553 * Manipulate port table per dispatch: find an entry for a given port number,
554 * create a new entry, and decrement a given entry with possible clean-up.
555 */
556static dispportentry_t *
557port_search(dns_dispatch_t *disp, in_port_t port) {
558 dispportentry_t *portentry;
559
560 REQUIRE(disp->port_table != NULL);
561
562 portentry = ISC_LIST_HEAD(disp->port_table[port %
563 DNS_DISPATCH_PORTTABLESIZE]);
564 while (portentry != NULL) {
565 if (portentry->port == port)
566 return (portentry);
567 portentry = ISC_LIST_NEXT(portentry, link);
568 }
569
570 return (NULL);
571}
572
573static dispportentry_t *
574new_portentry(dns_dispatch_t *disp, in_port_t port) {
575 dispportentry_t *portentry;
576 dns_qid_t *qid;
577
578 REQUIRE(disp->port_table != NULL);
579
580 portentry = isc_mempool_get(disp->portpool);
581 if (portentry == NULL)
582 return (portentry);
583
584 portentry->port = port;
585 portentry->refs = 1;
586 ISC_LINK_INIT(portentry, link);
587 qid = DNS_QID(disp);
588 LOCK(&qid->lock);
589 ISC_LIST_APPEND(disp->port_table[port % DNS_DISPATCH_PORTTABLESIZE],
590 portentry, link);
591 UNLOCK(&qid->lock);
592
593 return (portentry);
594}
595
596/*%
597 * The caller must not hold the qid->lock.
598 */
599static void
600deref_portentry(dns_dispatch_t *disp, dispportentry_t **portentryp) {
601 dispportentry_t *portentry = *portentryp;
602 dns_qid_t *qid;
603
604 REQUIRE(disp->port_table != NULL);
605 REQUIRE(portentry != NULL && portentry->refs > 0);
606
607 qid = DNS_QID(disp);
608 LOCK(&qid->lock);
609 portentry->refs--;
610
611 if (portentry->refs == 0) {
612 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(disp->port_table[portentry->port %
613 DNS_DISPATCH_PORTTABLESIZE],
614 portentry, link);
615 isc_mempool_put(disp->portpool, portentry);
616 }
617
618 /*
619 * Set '*portentryp' to NULL inside the lock so that
620 * dispsock->portentry does not change in socket_search.
621 */
622 *portentryp = NULL;
623
624 UNLOCK(&qid->lock);
625}
626
627/*%
628 * Find a dispsocket for socket address 'dest', and port number 'port'.
629 * Return NULL if no such entry exists. Requires qid->lock to be held.
630 */
631static dispsocket_t *
632socket_search(dns_qid_t *qid, const isc_sockaddr_t *dest, in_port_t port,
633 unsigned int bucket)
634{
635 dispsocket_t *dispsock;
636
637 REQUIRE(VALID_QID(qid));
638 REQUIRE(bucket < qid->qid_nbuckets);
639
640 dispsock = ISC_LIST_HEAD(qid->sock_table[bucket]);
641
642 while (dispsock != NULL) {
643 if (dispsock->portentry != NULL &&
644 dispsock->portentry->port == port &&
645 isc_sockaddr_equal(dest, &dispsock->host))
646 return (dispsock);
647 dispsock = ISC_LIST_NEXT(dispsock, blink);
648 }
649
650 return (NULL);
651}

653/*%
654 * Make a new socket for a single dispatch with a random port number.
655 * The caller must hold the disp->lock
656 */
657static isc_result_t
658get_dispsocket(dns_dispatch_t *disp, const isc_sockaddr_t *dest,
659 isc_socketmgr_t *sockmgr, dispsocket_t **dispsockp,
660 in_port_t *portp)
661{
662 int i;
663 dns_dispatchmgr_t *mgr = disp->mgr;
664 isc_socket_t *sock = NULL;
665 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
666 in_port_t port;
667 isc_sockaddr_t localaddr;
668 unsigned int bucket = 0;
669 dispsocket_t *dispsock;
670 unsigned int nports;
671 in_port_t *ports;
672 isc_socket_options_t bindoptions;
673 dispportentry_t *portentry = NULL;
674 dns_qid_t *qid;
675
676 if (isc_sockaddr_pf(&disp->local) == AF_INET) {
677 nports = disp->mgr->nv4ports;
678 ports = disp->mgr->v4ports;
679 } else {
680 nports = disp->mgr->nv6ports;
681 ports = disp->mgr->v6ports;
682 }
683 if (nports == 0)
684 return (ISC_R_ADDRNOTAVAIL);
685
686 dispsock = ISC_LIST_HEAD(disp->inactivesockets);
687 if (dispsock != NULL) {
688 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(disp->inactivesockets, dispsock, link);
689 sock = dispsock->socket;
690 dispsock->socket = NULL;
691 } else {
692 dispsock = isc_mempool_get(mgr->spool);
693 if (dispsock == NULL)
694 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
695
696 disp->nsockets++;
697 dispsock->socket = NULL;
698 dispsock->disp = disp;
699 dispsock->resp = NULL;
700 dispsock->portentry = NULL;
701 dispsock->task = NULL;
702 isc_task_attach(disp->task[isc_random_uniform(disp->ntasks)],
703 &dispsock->task);
704 ISC_LINK_INIT(dispsock, link);
705 ISC_LINK_INIT(dispsock, blink);
706 dispsock->magic = DISPSOCK_MAGIC;
707 }
708
709 /*
710 * Pick up a random UDP port and open a new socket with it. Avoid
711 * choosing ports that share the same destination because it will be
712 * very likely to fail in bind(2) or connect(2).
713 */
714 localaddr = disp->local;
715 qid = DNS_QID(disp);
716
717 for (i = 0; i < 64; i++) {
718 port = ports[isc_random_uniform(nports)];
719 isc_sockaddr_setport(&localaddr, port);
720
721 LOCK(&qid->lock);
722 bucket = dns_hash(qid, dest, 0, port);
723 if (socket_search(qid, dest, port, bucket) != NULL) {
724 UNLOCK(&qid->lock);
725 continue;
726 }
727 UNLOCK(&qid->lock);
728 bindoptions = 0;
729 portentry = port_search(disp, port);
730
731 if (portentry != NULL)
732 bindoptions |= ISC_SOCKET_REUSEADDRESS;
733 result = open_socket(sockmgr, &localaddr, bindoptions, &sock,
734 NULL, false);
735 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
736 if (portentry == NULL) {
737 portentry = new_portentry(disp, port);
738 if (portentry == NULL) {
739 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
740 break;
741 }
742 } else {
743 LOCK(&qid->lock);
744 portentry->refs++;
745 UNLOCK(&qid->lock);
746 }
747 break;
748 } else if (result == ISC_R_NOPERM) {
749 char buf[ISC_SOCKADDR_FORMATSIZE];
750 isc_sockaddr_format(&localaddr, buf, sizeof(buf));
751 dispatch_log(disp, ISC_LOG_WARNING,
752 "open_socket(%s) -> %s: continuing",
753 buf, isc_result_totext(result));
754 } else if (result != ISC_R_ADDRINUSE)
755 break;
756 }
757
758 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
759 dispsock->socket = sock;
760 dispsock->host = *dest;
761 dispsock->portentry = portentry;
762 dispsock->bucket = bucket;
763 LOCK(&qid->lock);
764 ISC_LIST_APPEND(qid->sock_table[bucket], dispsock, blink);
765 UNLOCK(&qid->lock);
766 *dispsockp = dispsock;
767 *portp = port;
768 } else {
769 /*
770 * We could keep it in the inactive list, but since this should
771 * be an exceptional case and might be resource shortage, we'd
772 * rather destroy it.
773 */
774 if (sock != NULL)
775 isc_socket_detach(&sock);
776 destroy_dispsocket(disp, &dispsock);
777 }
778
779 return (result);
780}
781
782/*%
783 * Destroy a dedicated dispatch socket.
784 */
785static void
786destroy_dispsocket(dns_dispatch_t *disp, dispsocket_t **dispsockp) {
787 dispsocket_t *dispsock;
788 dns_qid_t *qid;
789
790 /*
791 * The dispatch must be locked.
792 */
793
794 REQUIRE(dispsockp != NULL && *dispsockp != NULL);
795 dispsock = *dispsockp;
796 REQUIRE(!ISC_LINK_LINKED(dispsock, link));
797
798 disp->nsockets--;
799 dispsock->magic = 0;
800 if (dispsock->portentry != NULL)
801 deref_portentry(disp, &dispsock->portentry);
802 if (dispsock->socket != NULL)
803 isc_socket_detach(&dispsock->socket);
804 if (ISC_LINK_LINKED(dispsock, blink)) {
805 qid = DNS_QID(disp);
806 LOCK(&qid->lock);
807 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(qid->sock_table[dispsock->bucket], dispsock,
808 blink);
809 UNLOCK(&qid->lock);
810 }
811 if (dispsock->task != NULL)
812 isc_task_detach(&dispsock->task);
813 isc_mempool_put(disp->mgr->spool, dispsock);
814
815 *dispsockp = NULL;
816}
817
818/*%
819 * Deactivate a dedicated dispatch socket. Move it to the inactive list for
820 * future reuse unless the total number of sockets are exceeding the maximum.
821 */
822static void
823deactivate_dispsocket(dns_dispatch_t *disp, dispsocket_t *dispsock) {
824 isc_result_t result;
825 dns_qid_t *qid;
826
827 /*
828 * The dispatch must be locked.
829 */
830 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(disp->activesockets, dispsock, link);
831 if (dispsock->resp != NULL) {
832 INSIST(dispsock->resp->dispsocket == dispsock);
833 dispsock->resp->dispsocket = NULL;
834 }
835
836 INSIST(dispsock->portentry != NULL);
837 deref_portentry(disp, &dispsock->portentry);
838
839 if (disp->nsockets > DNS_DISPATCH_POOLSOCKS)
840 destroy_dispsocket(disp, &dispsock);
841 else {
842 result = isc_socket_close(dispsock->socket);
843
844 qid = DNS_QID(disp);
845 LOCK(&qid->lock);
846 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(qid->sock_table[dispsock->bucket], dispsock,
847 blink);
848 UNLOCK(&qid->lock);
849
850 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
851 ISC_LIST_APPEND(disp->inactivesockets, dispsock, link);
852 else {
853 /*
854 * If the underlying system does not allow this
855 * optimization, destroy this temporary structure (and
856 * create a new one for a new transaction).
857 */
858 INSIST(result == ISC_R_NOTIMPLEMENTED);
859 destroy_dispsocket(disp, &dispsock);
860 }
861 }
862}
863
864/*
865 * Find an entry for query ID 'id', socket address 'dest', and port number
866 * 'port'.
867 * Return NULL if no such entry exists.
868 */
869static dns_dispentry_t *
870entry_search(dns_qid_t *qid, const isc_sockaddr_t *dest, dns_messageid_t id,
871 in_port_t port, unsigned int bucket)
872{
873 dns_dispentry_t *res;
874
875 REQUIRE(VALID_QID(qid));
876 REQUIRE(bucket < qid->qid_nbuckets);
877
878 res = ISC_LIST_HEAD(qid->qid_table[bucket]);
879
880 while (res != NULL) {
881 if (res->id == id && isc_sockaddr_equal(dest, &res->host) &&
882 res->port == port) {
883 return (res);
884 }
885 res = ISC_LIST_NEXT(res, link);
886 }
887
888 return (NULL);
889}
890
891static void
892free_buffer(dns_dispatch_t *disp, void *buf, unsigned int len) {
893 isc_mempool_t *bpool;
894 INSIST(buf != NULL && len != 0);
895
896
897 switch (disp->socktype) {
898 case isc_sockettype_tcp:
899 INSIST(disp->tcpbuffers > 0);
900 disp->tcpbuffers--;
901 isc_mem_put(disp->mgr->mctx, buf, len);
902 break;
903 case isc_sockettype_udp:
904 LOCK(&disp->mgr->buffer_lock);
905 INSIST(disp->mgr->buffers > 0);
906 INSIST(len == disp->mgr->buffersize);
907 disp->mgr->buffers--;
908 bpool = disp->mgr->bpool;
909 UNLOCK(&disp->mgr->buffer_lock);
910 isc_mempool_put(bpool, buf);
911 break;
912 default:
913 INSIST(0);
914 ISC_UNREACHABLE();
915 }
916}
917
918static void *
919allocate_udp_buffer(dns_dispatch_t *disp) {
920 isc_mempool_t *bpool;
921 void *temp;
922
923 LOCK(&disp->mgr->buffer_lock);
924 bpool = disp->mgr->bpool;
925 disp->mgr->buffers++;
926 UNLOCK(&disp->mgr->buffer_lock);
927
928 temp = isc_mempool_get(bpool);
929
930 if (temp == NULL) {
931 LOCK(&disp->mgr->buffer_lock);
932 disp->mgr->buffers--;
933 UNLOCK(&disp->mgr->buffer_lock);
934 }
935
936 return (temp);
937}

939static inline void
940free_sevent(isc_event_t *ev) {
941 isc_mempool_t *pool = ev->ev_destroy_arg;
942 isc_socketevent_t *sev = (isc_socketevent_t *) ev;
943 isc_mempool_put(pool, sev);
944}
945
946static inline isc_socketevent_t *
947allocate_sevent(dns_dispatch_t *disp, isc_socket_t *sock,
948 isc_eventtype_t type, isc_taskaction_t action, const void *arg)
949{
950 isc_socketevent_t *ev;
951 void *deconst_arg;
952
953 ev = isc_mempool_get(disp->sepool);
954 if (ev == NULL)
955 return (NULL);
956 DE_CONST(arg, deconst_arg);
957 ISC_EVENT_INIT(ev, sizeof(*ev), 0, NULL, type,
958 action, deconst_arg, sock,
959 free_sevent, disp->sepool);
960 ev->result = ISC_R_UNSET;
961 ISC_LINK_INIT(ev, ev_link);
962 ev->region.base = NULL;
963 ev->n = 0;
964 ev->offset = 0;
965 ev->attributes = 0;
966
967 return (ev);
968}

971static inline void
972free_devent(dns_dispatch_t *disp, dns_dispatchevent_t *ev) {
973 if (disp->failsafe_ev == ev) {
974 INSIST(disp->shutdown_out == 1);
975 disp->shutdown_out = 0;
976
977 return;
978 }
979
980 isc_mempool_put(disp->mgr->depool, ev);
981}

983static inline dns_dispatchevent_t *
984allocate_devent(dns_dispatch_t *disp) {
985 dns_dispatchevent_t *ev;
986
987 ev = isc_mempool_get(disp->mgr->depool);
988 if (ev == NULL)
989 return (NULL);
990 ISC_EVENT_INIT(ev, sizeof(*ev), 0, NULL, 0,
991 NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
992
993 return (ev);
994}

1015
1016/*
1017 * General flow:
1018 *
1019 * If I/O result == CANCELED or error, free the buffer.
1020 *
1021 * If query, free the buffer, restart.
1022 *
1023 * If response:
1024 * Allocate event, fill in details.
1025 * If cannot allocate, free buffer, restart.
1026 * find target. If not found, free buffer, restart.
1027 * if event queue is not empty, queue. else, send.
1028 * restart.
1029 */
1030static void
1031udp_recv(isc_event_t *ev_in, dns_dispatch_t *disp, dispsocket_t *dispsock) {
1032 isc_socketevent_t *ev = (isc_socketevent_t *)ev_in;
1033 dns_messageid_t id;
1034 isc_result_t dres;
1035 isc_buffer_t source;
1036 unsigned int flags;
1037 dns_dispentry_t *resp = NULL;
1038 dns_dispatchevent_t *rev;
1039 unsigned int bucket;
1040 bool killit;
1041 bool queue_response;
1042 dns_dispatchmgr_t *mgr;
1043 dns_qid_t *qid;
1044 isc_netaddr_t netaddr;
1045 int match;
1046 int result;
1047 bool qidlocked = false;
1048
1049 LOCK(&disp->lock);
1050
1051 mgr = disp->mgr;
1052 qid = mgr->qid;
1053
1054 dispatch_log(disp, LVL(90),
1055 "got packet: requests %d, buffers %d, recvs %d",
1056 disp->requests, disp->mgr->buffers, disp->recv_pending);
1057
1058 if (dispsock == NULL && ev->ev_type == ISC_SOCKEVENT_RECVDONE) {
1059 /*
1060 * Unless the receive event was imported from a listening
1061 * interface, in which case the event type is
1062 * DNS_EVENT_IMPORTRECVDONE, receive operation must be pending.
1063 */
1064 INSIST(disp->recv_pending != 0);
1065 disp->recv_pending = 0;
1066 }
1067
1068 if (dispsock != NULL &&
1069 (ev->result == ISC_R_CANCELED || dispsock->resp == NULL)) {
1070 /*
1071 * dispsock->resp can be NULL if this transaction was canceled
1072 * just after receiving a response. Since this socket is
1073 * exclusively used and there should be at most one receive
1074 * event the canceled event should have been no effect. So
1075 * we can (and should) deactivate the socket right now.
1076 */
1077 deactivate_dispsocket(disp, dispsock);
1078 dispsock = NULL;
1079 }
1080
1081 if (disp->shutting_down) {
1082 /*
1083 * This dispatcher is shutting down.
1084 */
1085 free_buffer(disp, ev->region.base, ev->region.length);
1086
1087 isc_event_free(&ev_in);
1088 ev = NULL;
1089
1090 killit = destroy_disp_ok(disp);
1091 UNLOCK(&disp->lock);
1092 if (killit)
1093 isc_task_send(disp->task[0], &disp->ctlevent);
1094
1095 return;
1096 }
1097
1098 if ((disp->attributes & DNS_DISPATCHATTR_EXCLUSIVE) != 0) {
1099 if (dispsock != NULL) {
1100 resp = dispsock->resp;
1101 id = resp->id;
1102 if (ev->result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1103 /*
1104 * This is most likely a network error on a
1105 * connected socket. It makes no sense to
1106 * check the address or parse the packet, but it
1107 * will help to return the error to the caller.
1108 */
1109 goto sendresponse;
1110 }
1111 } else {
1112 free_buffer(disp, ev->region.base, ev->region.length);
1113
1114 isc_event_free(&ev_in);
1115 UNLOCK(&disp->lock);
1116 return;
1117 }
1118 } else if (ev->result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1119 free_buffer(disp, ev->region.base, ev->region.length);
1120
1121 if (ev->result != ISC_R_CANCELED)
1122 dispatch_log(disp, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
1123 "odd socket result in udp_recv(): %s",
1124 isc_result_totext(ev->result));
1125
1126 isc_event_free(&ev_in);
1127 UNLOCK(&disp->lock);
1128 return;
1129 }
1130
1131 /*
1132 * If this is from a blackholed address, drop it.
1133 */
1134 isc_netaddr_fromsockaddr(&netaddr, &ev->address);
1135 if (disp->mgr->blackhole != NULL &&
1136 dns_acl_match(&netaddr, NULL, disp->mgr->blackhole,
1137 NULL, &match, NULL) == ISC_R_SUCCESS &&
1138 match > 0)
1139 {
1140 if (isc_log_wouldlog(dns_lctx, LVL(10))) {
1141 char netaddrstr[ISC_NETADDR_FORMATSIZE];
1142 isc_netaddr_format(&netaddr, netaddrstr,
1143 sizeof(netaddrstr));
1144 dispatch_log(disp, LVL(10),
1145 "blackholed packet from %s",
1146 netaddrstr);
1147 }
1148 free_buffer(disp, ev->region.base, ev->region.length);
1149 goto restart;
1150 }
1151
1152 /*
1153 * Peek into the buffer to see what we can see.
1154 */
1155 isc_buffer_init(&source, ev->region.base, ev->region.length);
1156 isc_buffer_add(&source, ev->n);
1157 dres = dns_message_peekheader(&source, &id, &flags);
1158 if (dres != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1159 free_buffer(disp, ev->region.base, ev->region.length);
1160 dispatch_log(disp, LVL(10), "got garbage packet");
1161 goto restart;
1162 }
1163
1164 dispatch_log(disp, LVL(92),
1165 "got valid DNS message header, /QR %c, id %u",
1166 (((flags & DNS_MESSAGEFLAG_QR) != 0) ? '1' : '0'), id);
1167
1168 /*
1169 * Look at flags. If query, drop it. If response,
1170 * look to see where it goes.
1171 */
1172 if ((flags & DNS_MESSAGEFLAG_QR) == 0) {
1173 /* query */
1174 free_buffer(disp, ev->region.base, ev->region.length);
1175 goto restart;
1176 }
1177
1178 /*
1179 * Search for the corresponding response. If we are using an exclusive
1180 * socket, we've already identified it and we can skip the search; but
1181 * the ID and the address must match the expected ones.
1182 */
1183 if (resp == NULL) {
1184 bucket = dns_hash(qid, &ev->address, id, disp->localport);
1185 LOCK(&qid->lock);
1186 qidlocked = true;
1187 resp = entry_search(qid, &ev->address, id, disp->localport,
1188 bucket);
1189 dispatch_log(disp, LVL(90),
1190 "search for response in bucket %d: %s",
1191 bucket, (resp == NULL ? "not found" : "found"));
1192
1193 if (resp == NULL) {
1194 inc_stats(mgr, dns_resstatscounter_mismatch);
1195 free_buffer(disp, ev->region.base, ev->region.length);
1196 goto unlock;
1197 }
1198 } else if (resp->id != id || !isc_sockaddr_equal(&ev->address,
1199 &resp->host)) {
1200 dispatch_log(disp, LVL(90),
1201 "response to an exclusive socket doesn't match");
1202 inc_stats(mgr, dns_resstatscounter_mismatch);
1203 free_buffer(disp, ev->region.base, ev->region.length);
1204 goto unlock;
1205 }
1206
1207 /*
1208 * Now that we have the original dispatch the query was sent
1209 * from check that the address and port the response was
1210 * sent to make sense.
1211 */
1212 if (disp != resp->disp) {
1213 isc_sockaddr_t a1;
1214 isc_sockaddr_t a2;
1215
1216 /*
1217 * Check that the socket types and ports match.
1218 */
1219 if (disp->socktype != resp->disp->socktype ||
1220 isc_sockaddr_getport(&disp->local) !=
1221 isc_sockaddr_getport(&resp->disp->local)) {
1222 free_buffer(disp, ev->region.base, ev->region.length);
1223 goto unlock;
1224 }
1225
1226 /*
1227 * If each dispatch is bound to a different address
1228 * then fail.
1229 *
1230 * Note under Linux a packet can be sent out via IPv4 socket
1231 * and the response be received via a IPv6 socket.
1232 *
1233 * Requests sent out via IPv6 should always come back in
1234 * via IPv6.
1235 */
1236 if (isc_sockaddr_pf(&resp->disp->local) == PF_INET6 &&
1237 isc_sockaddr_pf(&disp->local) != PF_INET6) {
1238 free_buffer(disp, ev->region.base, ev->region.length);
1239 goto unlock;
1240 }
1241 isc_sockaddr_anyofpf(&a1, isc_sockaddr_pf(&resp->disp->local));
1242 isc_sockaddr_anyofpf(&a2, isc_sockaddr_pf(&disp->local));
1243 if (!isc_sockaddr_eqaddr(&disp->local, &resp->disp->local) &&
1244 !isc_sockaddr_eqaddr(&a1, &resp->disp->local) &&
1245 !isc_sockaddr_eqaddr(&a2, &disp->local)) {
1246 free_buffer(disp, ev->region.base, ev->region.length);
1247 goto unlock;
1248 }
1249 }
1250
1251 sendresponse:
1252 queue_response = resp->item_out;
1253 rev = allocate_devent(resp->disp);
1254 if (rev == NULL) {
1255 free_buffer(disp, ev->region.base, ev->region.length);
1256 goto unlock;
1257 }
1258
1259 /*
1260 * At this point, rev contains the event we want to fill in, and
1261 * resp contains the information on the place to send it to.
1262 * Send the event off.
1263 */
1264 isc_buffer_init(&rev->buffer, ev->region.base, ev->region.length);
1265 isc_buffer_add(&rev->buffer, ev->n);
1266 rev->result = ev->result;
1267 rev->id = id;
1268 rev->addr = ev->address;
1269 rev->pktinfo = ev->pktinfo;
1270 rev->attributes = ev->attributes;
1271 if (queue_response) {
1272 ISC_LIST_APPEND(resp->items, rev, ev_link);
1273 } else {
1274 ISC_EVENT_INIT(rev, sizeof(*rev), 0, NULL,
1275 DNS_EVENT_DISPATCH,
1276 resp->action, resp->arg, resp, NULL, NULL);
1277 request_log(disp, resp, LVL(90),
1278 "[a] Sent event %p buffer %p len %d to task %p",
1279 rev, rev->buffer.base, rev->buffer.length,
1280 resp->task);
1281 resp->item_out = true;
1282 isc_task_send(resp->task, ISC_EVENT_PTR(&rev));
1283 }
1284 unlock:
1285 if (qidlocked)
1286 UNLOCK(&qid->lock);
1287
1288 /*
1289 * Restart recv() to get the next packet.
1290 */
1291 restart:
1292 result = startrecv(disp, dispsock);
1293 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS && dispsock != NULL) {
1294 /*
1295 * XXX: wired. There seems to be no recovery process other than
1296 * deactivate this socket anyway (since we cannot start
1297 * receiving, we won't be able to receive a cancel event
1298 * from the user).
1299 */
1300 deactivate_dispsocket(disp, dispsock);
1301 }
1302 isc_event_free(&ev_in);
1303 UNLOCK(&disp->lock);
1304}
1305
1306/*
1307 * General flow:
1308 *
1309 * If I/O result == CANCELED, EOF, or error, notify everyone as the
1310 * various queues drain.
1311 *
1312 * If query, restart.
1313 *
1314 * If response:
1315 * Allocate event, fill in details.
1316 * If cannot allocate, restart.
1317 * find target. If not found, restart.
1318 * if event queue is not empty, queue. else, send.
1319 * restart.
1320 */
1321static void
1322tcp_recv(isc_task_t *task, isc_event_t *ev_in) {
1323 dns_dispatch_t *disp = ev_in->ev_arg;
1324 dns_tcpmsg_t *tcpmsg = &disp->tcpmsg;
1325 dns_messageid_t id;
1326 isc_result_t dres;
1327 unsigned int flags;
1328 dns_dispentry_t *resp;
1329 dns_dispatchevent_t *rev;
1330 unsigned int bucket;
1331 bool killit;
1332 bool queue_response;
1333 dns_qid_t *qid;
1334 int level;
1335 char buf[ISC_SOCKADDR_FORMATSIZE];
1336
1337 UNUSED(task);
1338
1339 REQUIRE(VALID_DISPATCH(disp));
1340
1341 qid = disp->qid;
1342
1343 dispatch_log(disp, LVL(90),
1344 "got TCP packet: requests %d, buffers %d, recvs %d",
1345 disp->requests, disp->tcpbuffers, disp->recv_pending);
1346
1347 LOCK(&disp->lock);
1348
1349 INSIST(disp->recv_pending != 0);
1350 disp->recv_pending = 0;
1351
1352 if (disp->refcount == 0) {
1353 /*
1354 * This dispatcher is shutting down. Force cancelation.
1355 */
1356 tcpmsg->result = ISC_R_CANCELED;
1357 }
1358
1359 if (tcpmsg->result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1360 switch (tcpmsg->result) {
1361 case ISC_R_CANCELED:
1362 break;
1363
1364 case ISC_R_EOF:
1365 dispatch_log(disp, LVL(90), "shutting down on EOF");
1366 do_cancel(disp);
1367 break;
1368
1369 case ISC_R_CONNECTIONRESET:
1370 level = ISC_LOG_INFO;
1371 goto logit;
1372
1373 default:
1374 level = ISC_LOG_ERROR;
1375 logit:
1376 isc_sockaddr_format(&tcpmsg->address, buf, sizeof(buf));
1377 dispatch_log(disp, level, "shutting down due to TCP "
1378 "receive error: %s: %s", buf,
1379 isc_result_totext(tcpmsg->result));
1380 do_cancel(disp);
1381 break;
1382 }
1383
1384 /*
1385 * The event is statically allocated in the tcpmsg
1386 * structure, and destroy_disp() frees the tcpmsg, so we must
1387 * free the event *before* calling destroy_disp().
1388 */
1389 isc_event_free(&ev_in);
1390
1391 disp->shutting_down = 1;
1392 disp->shutdown_why = tcpmsg->result;
1393
1394 /*
1395 * If the recv() was canceled pass the word on.
1396 */
1397 killit = destroy_disp_ok(disp);
1398 UNLOCK(&disp->lock);
1399 if (killit)
1400 isc_task_send(disp->task[0], &disp->ctlevent);
1401 return;
1402 }
1403
1404 dispatch_log(disp, LVL(90), "result %d, length == %d, addr = %p",
1405 tcpmsg->result,
1406 tcpmsg->buffer.length, tcpmsg->buffer.base);
1407
1408 /*
1409 * Peek into the buffer to see what we can see.
1410 */
1411 dres = dns_message_peekheader(&tcpmsg->buffer, &id, &flags);
1412 if (dres != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1413 dispatch_log(disp, LVL(10), "got garbage packet");
1414 goto restart;
1415 }
1416
1417 dispatch_log(disp, LVL(92),
1418 "got valid DNS message header, /QR %c, id %u",
1419 (((flags & DNS_MESSAGEFLAG_QR) != 0) ? '1' : '0'), id);
1420
1421 /*
1422 * Allocate an event to send to the query or response client, and
1423 * allocate a new buffer for our use.
1424 */
1425
1426 /*
1427 * Look at flags. If query, drop it. If response,
1428 * look to see where it goes.
1429 */
1430 if ((flags & DNS_MESSAGEFLAG_QR) == 0) {
1431 /*
1432 * Query.
1433 */
1434 goto restart;
1435 }
1436
1437 /*
1438 * Response.
1439 */
1440 bucket = dns_hash(qid, &tcpmsg->address, id, disp->localport);
1441 LOCK(&qid->lock);
1442 resp = entry_search(qid, &tcpmsg->address, id, disp->localport, bucket);
1443 dispatch_log(disp, LVL(90),
1444 "search for response in bucket %d: %s",
1445 bucket, (resp == NULL ? "not found" : "found"));
1446
1447 if (resp == NULL)
1448 goto unlock;
1449 queue_response = resp->item_out;
1450 rev = allocate_devent(disp);
1451 if (rev == NULL)
1452 goto unlock;
1453
1454 /*
1455 * At this point, rev contains the event we want to fill in, and
1456 * resp contains the information on the place to send it to.
1457 * Send the event off.
1458 */
1459 dns_tcpmsg_keepbuffer(tcpmsg, &rev->buffer);
1460 disp->tcpbuffers++;
1461 rev->result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
1462 rev->id = id;
1463 rev->addr = tcpmsg->address;
1464 if (queue_response) {
1465 ISC_LIST_APPEND(resp->items, rev, ev_link);
1466 } else {
1467 ISC_EVENT_INIT(rev, sizeof(*rev), 0, NULL, DNS_EVENT_DISPATCH,
1468 resp->action, resp->arg, resp, NULL, NULL);
1469 request_log(disp, resp, LVL(90),
1470 "[b] Sent event %p buffer %p len %d to task %p",
1471 rev, rev->buffer.base, rev->buffer.length,
1472 resp->task);
1473 resp->item_out = true;
1474 isc_task_send(resp->task, ISC_EVENT_PTR(&rev));
1475 }
1476 unlock:
1477 UNLOCK(&qid->lock);
1478
1479 /*
1480 * Restart recv() to get the next packet.
1481 */
1482 restart:
1483 (void)startrecv(disp, NULL);
1484
1485 isc_event_free(&ev_in);
1486 UNLOCK(&disp->lock);
1487}
1488
1489/*
1490 * disp must be locked.
1491 */
1492static isc_result_t
1493startrecv(dns_dispatch_t *disp, dispsocket_t *dispsock) {
1494 isc_result_t res;
1495 isc_region_t region;
1496 isc_socket_t *sock;
1497
1498 if (disp->shutting_down == 1)
1499 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
1500
1501 if ((disp->attributes & DNS_DISPATCHATTR_NOLISTEN) != 0)
1502 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
1503
1504 if (disp->recv_pending != 0 && dispsock == NULL)
1505 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
1506
1507 if (disp->mgr->buffers >= disp->mgr->maxbuffers)
1508 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
1509
1510 if ((disp->attributes & DNS_DISPATCHATTR_EXCLUSIVE) != 0 &&
1511 dispsock == NULL)
1512 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
1513
1514 if (dispsock != NULL)
1515 sock = dispsock->socket;
1516 else
1517 sock = disp->socket;
1518 INSIST(sock != NULL);
1519
1520 switch (disp->socktype) {
1521 /*
1522 * UDP reads are always maximal.
1523 */
1524 case isc_sockettype_udp:
1525 region.length = disp->mgr->buffersize;
1526 region.base = allocate_udp_buffer(disp);
1527 if (region.base == NULL)
1528 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
1529 if (dispsock != NULL) {
1530 isc_task_t *dt = dispsock->task;
1531 isc_socketevent_t *sev =
1532 allocate_sevent(disp, sock,
1533 ISC_SOCKEVENT_RECVDONE,
1534 udp_exrecv, dispsock);
1535 if (sev == NULL) {
1536 free_buffer(disp, region.base, region.length);
1537 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
1538 }
1539
1540 res = isc_socket_recv2(sock, &region, 1, dt, sev, 0);
1541 if (res != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1542 free_buffer(disp, region.base, region.length);
1543 return (res);
1544 }
1545 } else {
1546 isc_task_t *dt = disp->task[0];
1547 isc_socketevent_t *sev =
1548 allocate_sevent(disp, sock,
1549 ISC_SOCKEVENT_RECVDONE,
1550 udp_shrecv, disp);
1551 if (sev == NULL) {
1552 free_buffer(disp, region.base, region.length);
1553 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
1554 }
1555
1556 res = isc_socket_recv2(sock, &region, 1, dt, sev, 0);
1557 if (res != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1558 free_buffer(disp, region.base, region.length);
1559 disp->shutdown_why = res;
1560 disp->shutting_down = 1;
1561 do_cancel(disp);
1562 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS); /* recover by cancel */
1563 }
1564 INSIST(disp->recv_pending == 0);
1565 disp->recv_pending = 1;
1566 }
1567 break;
1568
1569 case isc_sockettype_tcp:
1570 res = dns_tcpmsg_readmessage(&disp->tcpmsg, disp->task[0],
1571 tcp_recv, disp);
1572 if (res != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1573 disp->shutdown_why = res;
1574 disp->shutting_down = 1;
1575 do_cancel(disp);
1576 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS); /* recover by cancel */
1577 }
1578 INSIST(disp->recv_pending == 0);
1579 disp->recv_pending = 1;
1580 break;
1581 default:
1582 INSIST(0);
1583 ISC_UNREACHABLE();
1584 }
1585
1586 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
1587}
1588
1589/*
1590 * Mgr must be locked when calling this function.
1591 */
1592static bool
1593destroy_mgr_ok(dns_dispatchmgr_t *mgr) {
1594 mgr_log(mgr, LVL(90),
1595 "destroy_mgr_ok: shuttingdown=%d, listnonempty=%d, "
1596 "depool=%d, rpool=%d, dpool=%d",
1597 MGR_IS_SHUTTINGDOWN(mgr), !ISC_LIST_EMPTY(mgr->list),
1598 isc_mempool_getallocated(mgr->depool),
1599 isc_mempool_getallocated(mgr->rpool),
1600 isc_mempool_getallocated(mgr->dpool));
1601 if (!MGR_IS_SHUTTINGDOWN(mgr))
1602 return (false);
1603 if (!ISC_LIST_EMPTY(mgr->list))
1604 return (false);
1605 if (isc_mempool_getallocated(mgr->depool) != 0)
1606 return (false);
1607 if (isc_mempool_getallocated(mgr->rpool) != 0)
1608 return (false);
1609 if (isc_mempool_getallocated(mgr->dpool) != 0)
1610 return (false);
1611
1612 return (true);
1613}
1614
1615/*
1616 * Mgr must be unlocked when calling this function.
1617 */
1618static void
1619destroy_mgr(dns_dispatchmgr_t **mgrp) {
1620 isc_mem_t *mctx;
1621 dns_dispatchmgr_t *mgr;
1622
1623 mgr = *mgrp;
1624 *mgrp = NULL;
1625
1626 mctx = mgr->mctx;
1627
1628 mgr->magic = 0;
1629 mgr->mctx = NULL;
1630 isc_mutex_destroy(&mgr->lock);
1631 mgr->state = 0;
1632
1633 isc_mempool_destroy(&mgr->depool);
1634 isc_mempool_destroy(&mgr->rpool);
1635 isc_mempool_destroy(&mgr->dpool);
1636 if (mgr->bpool != NULL)
1637 isc_mempool_destroy(&mgr->bpool);
1638 if (mgr->spool != NULL)
1639 isc_mempool_destroy(&mgr->spool);
1640
1641 isc_mutex_destroy(&mgr->spool_lock);
1642 isc_mutex_destroy(&mgr->bpool_lock);
1643 isc_mutex_destroy(&mgr->dpool_lock);
1644 isc_mutex_destroy(&mgr->rpool_lock);
1645 isc_mutex_destroy(&mgr->depool_lock);
1646
1647 if (mgr->qid != NULL)
1648 qid_destroy(mctx, &mgr->qid);
1649
1650 isc_mutex_destroy(&mgr->buffer_lock);
1651
1652 if (mgr->blackhole != NULL)
1653 dns_acl_detach(&mgr->blackhole);
1654
1655 if (mgr->stats != NULL)
1656 isc_stats_detach(&mgr->stats);
1657
1658 if (mgr->v4ports != NULL) {
1659 isc_mem_put(mctx, mgr->v4ports,
1660 mgr->nv4ports * sizeof(in_port_t));
1661 }
1662 if (mgr->v6ports != NULL) {
1663 isc_mem_put(mctx, mgr->v6ports,
1664 mgr->nv6ports * sizeof(in_port_t));
1665 }
1666 isc_mem_put(mctx, mgr, sizeof(dns_dispatchmgr_t));
1667 isc_mem_detach(&mctx);
1668}
1669
1670static isc_result_t
1671open_socket(isc_socketmgr_t *mgr, const isc_sockaddr_t *local,
1672 unsigned int options, isc_socket_t **sockp,
1673 isc_socket_t *dup_socket, bool duponly)
1674{
1675 isc_socket_t *sock;
1676 isc_result_t result;
1677
1678 sock = *sockp;
1679 if (sock != NULL) {
1680 result = isc_socket_open(sock);
1681 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1682 return (result);
1683 }
1684 } else if (dup_socket != NULL &&
1685 (!isc_socket_hasreuseport() || duponly))
1686 {
1687 result = isc_socket_dup(dup_socket, &sock);
1688 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1689 return (result);
1690 }
1691
1692 isc_socket_setname(sock, "dispatcher", NULL);
1693 *sockp = sock;
1694 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
1695 } else {
1696 result = isc_socket_create(mgr, isc_sockaddr_pf(local),
1697 isc_sockettype_udp, &sock);
1698 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1699 return (result);
1700 }
1701 }
1702
1703 isc_socket_setname(sock, "dispatcher", NULL);
1704
1705#ifndef ISC_ALLOW_MAPPED
1706 isc_socket_ipv6only(sock, true);
1707#endif
1708 result = isc_socket_bind(sock, local, options);
1709 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1710 if (*sockp == NULL) {
1711 isc_socket_detach(&sock);
1712 } else {
1713 isc_socket_close(sock);
1714 }
1715 return (result);
1716 }
1717
1718 *sockp = sock;
1719 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
1720}
1721
1722/*%
1723 * Create a temporary port list to set the initial default set of dispatch
1724 * ports: [1024, 65535]. This is almost meaningless as the application will
1725 * normally set the ports explicitly, but is provided to fill some minor corner
1726 * cases.
1727 */
1728static isc_result_t
1729create_default_portset(isc_mem_t *mctx, isc_portset_t **portsetp) {
1730 isc_result_t result;
1731
1732 result = isc_portset_create(mctx, portsetp);
1733 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1734 return (result);
1735 isc_portset_addrange(*portsetp, 1024, 65535);
1736
1737 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
1738}
1739
1740/*
1741 * Publics.
1742 */
1743
1744isc_result_t
1745dns_dispatchmgr_create(isc_mem_t *mctx, dns_dispatchmgr_t **mgrp)
1746{
1747 dns_dispatchmgr_t *mgr;
1748 isc_result_t result;
1749 isc_portset_t *v4portset = NULL;
1750 isc_portset_t *v6portset = NULL;
1751
1752 REQUIRE(mctx != NULL);
1753 REQUIRE(mgrp != NULL && *mgrp == NULL);
1754
1755 mgr = isc_mem_get(mctx, sizeof(dns_dispatchmgr_t));
1756 if (mgr == NULL)
1757 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
1758
1759 mgr->mctx = NULL;
1760 isc_mem_attach(mctx, &mgr->mctx);
1761
1762 mgr->blackhole = NULL;
1763 mgr->stats = NULL;
1764
1765 isc_mutex_init(&mgr->lock);
1766 isc_mutex_init(&mgr->buffer_lock);
1767 isc_mutex_init(&mgr->depool_lock);
1768 isc_mutex_init(&mgr->rpool_lock);
1769 isc_mutex_init(&mgr->dpool_lock);
1770 isc_mutex_init(&mgr->bpool_lock);
1771 isc_mutex_init(&mgr->spool_lock);
1772
1773 mgr->depool = NULL;
1774 if (isc_mempool_create(mgr->mctx, sizeof(dns_dispatchevent_t),
1775 &mgr->depool) != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1776 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
1777 goto kill_locks;
1778 }
1779
1780 mgr->rpool = NULL;
1781 if (isc_mempool_create(mgr->mctx, sizeof(dns_dispentry_t),
1782 &mgr->rpool) != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1783 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
1784 goto kill_depool;
1785 }
1786
1787 mgr->dpool = NULL;
1788 if (isc_mempool_create(mgr->mctx, sizeof(dns_dispatch_t),
1789 &mgr->dpool) != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1790 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
1791 goto kill_rpool;
1792 }
1793
1794 isc_mempool_setname(mgr->depool, "dispmgr_depool");
1795 isc_mempool_setmaxalloc(mgr->depool, 32768);
1796 isc_mempool_setfreemax(mgr->depool, 32768);
1797 isc_mempool_associatelock(mgr->depool, &mgr->depool_lock);
1798 isc_mempool_setfillcount(mgr->depool, 32);
1799
1800 isc_mempool_setname(mgr->rpool, "dispmgr_rpool");
1801 isc_mempool_setmaxalloc(mgr->rpool, 32768);
1802 isc_mempool_setfreemax(mgr->rpool, 32768);
1803 isc_mempool_associatelock(mgr->rpool, &mgr->rpool_lock);
1804 isc_mempool_setfillcount(mgr->rpool, 32);
1805
1806 isc_mempool_setname(mgr->dpool, "dispmgr_dpool");
1807 isc_mempool_setmaxalloc(mgr->dpool, 32768);
1808 isc_mempool_setfreemax(mgr->dpool, 32768);
1809 isc_mempool_associatelock(mgr->dpool, &mgr->dpool_lock);
1810 isc_mempool_setfillcount(mgr->dpool, 32);
1811
1812 mgr->buffers = 0;
1813 mgr->buffersize = 0;
1814 mgr->maxbuffers = 0;
1815 mgr->bpool = NULL;
1816 mgr->spool = NULL;
1817 mgr->qid = NULL;
1818 mgr->state = 0;
1819 ISC_LIST_INIT(mgr->list);
1820 mgr->v4ports = NULL;
1821 mgr->v6ports = NULL;
1822 mgr->nv4ports = 0;
1823 mgr->nv6ports = 0;
1824 mgr->magic = DNS_DISPATCHMGR_MAGIC;
1825
1826 result = create_default_portset(mctx, &v4portset);
1827 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1828 result = create_default_portset(mctx, &v6portset);
1829 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1830 result = dns_dispatchmgr_setavailports(mgr,
1831 v4portset,
1832 v6portset);
1833 }
1834 }
1835 if (v4portset != NULL)
1836 isc_portset_destroy(mctx, &v4portset);
1837 if (v6portset != NULL)
1838 isc_portset_destroy(mctx, &v6portset);
1839 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1840 goto kill_dpool;
1841
1842 *mgrp = mgr;
1843 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
1844
1845 kill_dpool:
1846 isc_mempool_destroy(&mgr->dpool);
1847 kill_rpool:
1848 isc_mempool_destroy(&mgr->rpool);
1849 kill_depool:
1850 isc_mempool_destroy(&mgr->depool);
1851 kill_locks:
1852 isc_mutex_destroy(&mgr->spool_lock);
1853 isc_mutex_destroy(&mgr->bpool_lock);
1854 isc_mutex_destroy(&mgr->dpool_lock);
1855 isc_mutex_destroy(&mgr->rpool_lock);
1856 isc_mutex_destroy(&mgr->depool_lock);
1857 isc_mutex_destroy(&mgr->buffer_lock);
1858 isc_mutex_destroy(&mgr->lock);
1859 isc_mem_put(mctx, mgr, sizeof(dns_dispatchmgr_t));
1860 isc_mem_detach(&mctx);
1861
1862 return (result);
1863}

1895
1896isc_result_t
1897dns_dispatchmgr_setavailports(dns_dispatchmgr_t *mgr, isc_portset_t *v4portset,
1898 isc_portset_t *v6portset)
1899{
1900 in_port_t *v4ports, *v6ports, p;
1901 unsigned int nv4ports, nv6ports, i4, i6;
1902
1903 REQUIRE(VALID_DISPATCHMGR(mgr));
1904
1905 nv4ports = isc_portset_nports(v4portset);
1906 nv6ports = isc_portset_nports(v6portset);
1907
1908 v4ports = NULL;
1909 if (nv4ports != 0) {
1910 v4ports = isc_mem_get(mgr->mctx, sizeof(in_port_t) * nv4ports);
1911 if (v4ports == NULL)
1912 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
1913 }
1914 v6ports = NULL;
1915 if (nv6ports != 0) {
1916 v6ports = isc_mem_get(mgr->mctx, sizeof(in_port_t) * nv6ports);
1917 if (v6ports == NULL) {
1918 if (v4ports != NULL) {
1919 isc_mem_put(mgr->mctx, v4ports,
1920 sizeof(in_port_t) *
1921 isc_portset_nports(v4portset));
1922 }
1923 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
1924 }
1925 }
1926
1927 p = 0;
1928 i4 = 0;
1929 i6 = 0;
1930 do {
1931 if (isc_portset_isset(v4portset, p)) {
1932 INSIST(i4 < nv4ports);
1933 v4ports[i4++] = p;
1934 }
1935 if (isc_portset_isset(v6portset, p)) {
1936 INSIST(i6 < nv6ports);
1937 v6ports[i6++] = p;
1938 }
1939 } while (p++ < 65535);
1940 INSIST(i4 == nv4ports && i6 == nv6ports);
1941
1942 PORTBUFLOCK(mgr);
1943 if (mgr->v4ports != NULL) {
1944 isc_mem_put(mgr->mctx, mgr->v4ports,
1945 mgr->nv4ports * sizeof(in_port_t));
1946 }
1947 mgr->v4ports = v4ports;
1948 mgr->nv4ports = nv4ports;
1949
1950 if (mgr->v6ports != NULL) {
1951 isc_mem_put(mgr->mctx, mgr->v6ports,
1952 mgr->nv6ports * sizeof(in_port_t));
1953 }
1954 mgr->v6ports = v6ports;
1955 mgr->nv6ports = nv6ports;
1956 PORTBUFUNLOCK(mgr);
1957
1958 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
1959}
1960
1961static isc_result_t
1962dns_dispatchmgr_setudp(dns_dispatchmgr_t *mgr,
1963 unsigned int buffersize, unsigned int maxbuffers,
1964 unsigned int maxrequests, unsigned int buckets,
1965 unsigned int increment)
1966{
1967 isc_result_t result;
1968
1969 REQUIRE(VALID_DISPATCHMGR(mgr));
1970 REQUIRE(buffersize >= 512 && buffersize < (64 * 1024));
1971 REQUIRE(maxbuffers > 0);
1972 REQUIRE(buckets < 2097169); /* next prime > 65536 * 32 */
1973 REQUIRE(increment > buckets);
1974
1975 /*
1976 * Keep some number of items around. This should be a config
1977 * option. For now, keep 8, but later keep at least two even
1978 * if the caller wants less. This allows us to ensure certain
1979 * things, like an event can be "freed" and the next allocation
1980 * will always succeed.
1981 *
1982 * Note that if limits are placed on anything here, we use one
1983 * event internally, so the actual limit should be "wanted + 1."
1984 *
1985 * XXXMLG
1986 */
1987
1988 if (maxbuffers < 8)
1989 maxbuffers = 8;
1990
1991 LOCK(&mgr->buffer_lock);
1992
1993 /* Create or adjust buffer pool */
1994 if (mgr->bpool != NULL) {
1995 /*
1996 * We only increase the maxbuffers to avoid accidental buffer
1997 * shortage. Ideally we'd separate the manager-wide maximum
1998 * from per-dispatch limits and respect the latter within the
1999 * global limit. But at this moment that's deemed to be
2000 * overkilling and isn't worth additional implementation
2001 * complexity.
2002 */
2003 if (maxbuffers > mgr->maxbuffers) {
2004 isc_mempool_setmaxalloc(mgr->bpool, maxbuffers);
2005 isc_mempool_setfreemax(mgr->bpool, maxbuffers);
2006 mgr->maxbuffers = maxbuffers;
2007 }
2008 } else {
2009 result = isc_mempool_create(mgr->mctx, buffersize, &mgr->bpool);
2010 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2011 UNLOCK(&mgr->buffer_lock);
2012 return (result);
2013 }
2014 isc_mempool_setname(mgr->bpool, "dispmgr_bpool");
2015 isc_mempool_setmaxalloc(mgr->bpool, maxbuffers);
2016 isc_mempool_setfreemax(mgr->bpool, maxbuffers);
2017 isc_mempool_associatelock(mgr->bpool, &mgr->bpool_lock);
2018 isc_mempool_setfillcount(mgr->bpool, 32);
2019 }
2020
2021 /* Create or adjust socket pool */
2022 if (mgr->spool != NULL) {
2023 if (maxrequests < DNS_DISPATCH_POOLSOCKS * 2) {
2024 isc_mempool_setmaxalloc(mgr->spool,
2025 DNS_DISPATCH_POOLSOCKS * 2);
2026 isc_mempool_setfreemax(mgr->spool,
2027 DNS_DISPATCH_POOLSOCKS * 2);
2028 }
2029 UNLOCK(&mgr->buffer_lock);
2030 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
2031 }
2032 result = isc_mempool_create(mgr->mctx, sizeof(dispsocket_t),
2033 &mgr->spool);
2034 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
2035 goto cleanup;
2036
2037 isc_mempool_setname(mgr->spool, "dispmgr_spool");
2038 isc_mempool_setmaxalloc(mgr->spool, maxrequests);
2039 isc_mempool_setfreemax(mgr->spool, maxrequests);
2040 isc_mempool_associatelock(mgr->spool, &mgr->spool_lock);
2041 isc_mempool_setfillcount(mgr->spool, 32);
2042
2043 result = qid_allocate(mgr, buckets, increment, &mgr->qid, true);
2044 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
2045 goto cleanup;
2046
2047 mgr->buffersize = buffersize;
2048 mgr->maxbuffers = maxbuffers;
2049 UNLOCK(&mgr->buffer_lock);
2050 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
2051
2052 cleanup:
2053 isc_mempool_destroy(&mgr->bpool);
2054 if (mgr->spool != NULL)
2055 isc_mempool_destroy(&mgr->spool);
2056 UNLOCK(&mgr->buffer_lock);
2057 return (result);
2058}

2091static int
2092port_cmp(const void *key, const void *ent) {
2093 in_port_t p1 = *(const in_port_t *)key;
2094 in_port_t p2 = *(const in_port_t *)ent;
2095
2096 if (p1 < p2)
2097 return (-1);
2098 else if (p1 == p2)
2099 return (0);
2100 else
2101 return (1);
2102}
2103
2104static bool
2105portavailable(dns_dispatchmgr_t *mgr, isc_socket_t *sock,
2106 isc_sockaddr_t *sockaddrp)
2107{
2108 isc_sockaddr_t sockaddr;
2109 isc_result_t result;
2110 in_port_t *ports, port;
2111 unsigned int nports;
2112 bool available = false;
2113
2114 REQUIRE(sock != NULL || sockaddrp != NULL);
2115
2116 PORTBUFLOCK(mgr);
2117 if (sock != NULL) {
2118 sockaddrp = &sockaddr;
2119 result = isc_socket_getsockname(sock, sockaddrp);
2120 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
2121 goto unlock;
2122 }
2123
2124 if (isc_sockaddr_pf(sockaddrp) == AF_INET) {
2125 ports = mgr->v4ports;
2126 nports = mgr->nv4ports;
2127 } else {
2128 ports = mgr->v6ports;
2129 nports = mgr->nv6ports;
2130 }
2131 if (ports == NULL)
2132 goto unlock;
2133
2134 port = isc_sockaddr_getport(sockaddrp);
2135 if (bsearch(&port, ports, nports, sizeof(in_port_t), port_cmp) != NULL)
2136 available = true;
2137
2138unlock:
2139 PORTBUFUNLOCK(mgr);
2140 return (available);
2141}

2143#define ATTRMATCH(_a1, _a2, _mask) (((_a1) & (_mask)) == ((_a2) & (_mask)))
2144
2145static bool
2146local_addr_match(dns_dispatch_t *disp, const isc_sockaddr_t *addr) {
2147 isc_sockaddr_t sockaddr;
2148 isc_result_t result;
2149
2150 REQUIRE(disp->socket != NULL);
2151
2152 if (addr == NULL)
2153 return (true);
2154
2155 /*
2156 * Don't match wildcard ports unless the port is available in the
2157 * current configuration.
2158 */
2159 if (isc_sockaddr_getport(addr) == 0 &&
2160 isc_sockaddr_getport(&disp->local) == 0 &&
2161 !portavailable(disp->mgr, disp->socket, NULL)) {
2162 return (false);
2163 }
2164
2165 /*
2166 * Check if we match the binding <address,port>.
2167 * Wildcard ports match/fail here.
2168 */
2169 if (isc_sockaddr_equal(&disp->local, addr))
2170 return (true);
2171 if (isc_sockaddr_getport(addr) == 0)
2172 return (false);
2173
2174 /*
2175 * Check if we match a bound wildcard port <address,port>.
2176 */
2177 if (!isc_sockaddr_eqaddr(&disp->local, addr))
2178 return (false);
2179 result = isc_socket_getsockname(disp->socket, &sockaddr);
2180 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
2181 return (false);
2182
2183 return (isc_sockaddr_equal(&sockaddr, addr));
2184}
2185
2186/*
2187 * Requires mgr be locked.
2188 *
2189 * No dispatcher can be locked by this thread when calling this function.
2190 *
2191 *
2192 * NOTE:
2193 * If a matching dispatcher is found, it is locked after this function
2194 * returns, and must be unlocked by the caller.
2195 */
2196static isc_result_t
2197dispatch_find(dns_dispatchmgr_t *mgr, const isc_sockaddr_t *local,
2198 unsigned int attributes, unsigned int mask,
2199 dns_dispatch_t **dispp)
2200{
2201 dns_dispatch_t *disp;
2202 isc_result_t result;
2203
2204 /*
2205 * Make certain that we will not match a private or exclusive dispatch.
2206 */
2207 attributes &= ~(DNS_DISPATCHATTR_PRIVATE|DNS_DISPATCHATTR_EXCLUSIVE);
2208 mask |= (DNS_DISPATCHATTR_PRIVATE|DNS_DISPATCHATTR_EXCLUSIVE);
2209
2210 disp = ISC_LIST_HEAD(mgr->list);
2211 while (disp != NULL) {
2212 LOCK(&disp->lock);
2213 if ((disp->shutting_down == 0)
2214 && ATTRMATCH(disp->attributes, attributes, mask)
2215 && local_addr_match(disp, local))
2216 break;
2217 UNLOCK(&disp->lock);
2218 disp = ISC_LIST_NEXT(disp, link);
2219 }
2220
2221 if (disp == NULL) {
2222 result = ISC_R_NOTFOUND;
2223 goto out;
2224 }
2225
2226 *dispp = disp;
2227 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
2228 out:
2229
2230 return (result);
2231}

2233static isc_result_t
2234qid_allocate(dns_dispatchmgr_t *mgr, unsigned int buckets,
2235 unsigned int increment, dns_qid_t **qidp,
2236 bool needsocktable)
2237{
2238 dns_qid_t *qid;
2239 unsigned int i;
2240
2241 REQUIRE(VALID_DISPATCHMGR(mgr));
2242 REQUIRE(buckets < 2097169); /* next prime > 65536 * 32 */
2243 REQUIRE(increment > buckets);
2244 REQUIRE(qidp != NULL && *qidp == NULL);
2245
2246 qid = isc_mem_get(mgr->mctx, sizeof(*qid));
2247 if (qid == NULL)
2248 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
2249
2250 qid->qid_table = isc_mem_get(mgr->mctx,
2251 buckets * sizeof(dns_displist_t));
2252 if (qid->qid_table == NULL) {
2253 isc_mem_put(mgr->mctx, qid, sizeof(*qid));
2254 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
2255 }
2256
2257 qid->sock_table = NULL;
2258 if (needsocktable) {
2259 qid->sock_table = isc_mem_get(mgr->mctx, buckets *
2260 sizeof(dispsocketlist_t));
2261 if (qid->sock_table == NULL) {
2262 isc_mem_put(mgr->mctx, qid->qid_table,
2263 buckets * sizeof(dns_displist_t));
2264 isc_mem_put(mgr->mctx, qid, sizeof(*qid));
2265 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
2266 }
2267 }
2268
2269 isc_mutex_init(&qid->lock);
2270
2271 for (i = 0; i < buckets; i++) {
2272 ISC_LIST_INIT(qid->qid_table[i]);
2273 if (qid->sock_table != NULL)
2274 ISC_LIST_INIT(qid->sock_table[i]);
2275 }
2276
2277 qid->qid_nbuckets = buckets;
2278 qid->qid_increment = increment;
2279 qid->magic = QID_MAGIC;
2280 *qidp = qid;
2281 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
2282}

2284static void
2285qid_destroy(isc_mem_t *mctx, dns_qid_t **qidp) {
2286 dns_qid_t *qid;
2287
2288 REQUIRE(qidp != NULL);
2289 qid = *qidp;
2290
2291 REQUIRE(VALID_QID(qid));
2292
2293 *qidp = NULL;
2294 qid->magic = 0;
2295 isc_mem_put(mctx, qid->qid_table,
2296 qid->qid_nbuckets * sizeof(dns_displist_t));
2297 if (qid->sock_table != NULL) {
2298 isc_mem_put(mctx, qid->sock_table,
2299 qid->qid_nbuckets * sizeof(dispsocketlist_t));
2300 }
2301 isc_mutex_destroy(&qid->lock);
2302 isc_mem_put(mctx, qid, sizeof(*qid));
2303}

2305/*
2306 * Allocate and set important limits.
2307 */
2308static isc_result_t
2309dispatch_allocate(dns_dispatchmgr_t *mgr, unsigned int maxrequests,
2310 dns_dispatch_t **dispp)
2311{
2312 dns_dispatch_t *disp;
2313 isc_result_t result;
2314
2315 REQUIRE(VALID_DISPATCHMGR(mgr));
2316 REQUIRE(dispp != NULL && *dispp == NULL);
2317
2318 /*
2319 * Set up the dispatcher, mostly. Don't bother setting some of
2320 * the options that are controlled by tcp vs. udp, etc.
2321 */
2322
2323 disp = isc_mempool_get(mgr->dpool);
2324 if (disp == NULL)
2325 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
2326
2327 disp->magic = 0;
2328 disp->mgr = mgr;
2329 disp->maxrequests = maxrequests;
2330 disp->attributes = 0;
2331 ISC_LINK_INIT(disp, link);
2332 disp->refcount = 1;
2333 disp->recv_pending = 0;
2334 memset(&disp->local, 0, sizeof(disp->local));
2335 memset(&disp->peer, 0, sizeof(disp->peer));
2336 disp->localport = 0;
2337 disp->shutting_down = 0;
2338 disp->shutdown_out = 0;
2339 disp->connected = 0;
2340 disp->tcpmsg_valid = 0;
2341 disp->shutdown_why = ISC_R_UNEXPECTED;
2342 disp->requests = 0;
2343 disp->tcpbuffers = 0;
2344 disp->qid = NULL;
2345 ISC_LIST_INIT(disp->activesockets);
2346 ISC_LIST_INIT(disp->inactivesockets);
2347 disp->nsockets = 0;
2348 disp->port_table = NULL;
2349 disp->portpool = NULL;
2350 disp->dscp = -1;
2351
2352 isc_mutex_init(&disp->lock);
2353
2354 disp->failsafe_ev = allocate_devent(disp);
2355 if (disp->failsafe_ev == NULL) {
2356 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
2357 goto kill_lock;
2358 }
2359
2360 disp->magic = DISPATCH_MAGIC;
2361
2362 *dispp = disp;
2363 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
2364
2365 /*
2366 * error returns
2367 */
2368 kill_lock:
2369 isc_mutex_destroy(&disp->lock);
2370 isc_mempool_put(mgr->dpool, disp);
2371
2372 return (result);
2373}

2376/*
2377 * MUST be unlocked, and not used by anything.
2378 */
2379static void
2380dispatch_free(dns_dispatch_t **dispp) {
2381 dns_dispatch_t *disp;
2382 dns_dispatchmgr_t *mgr;
2383 int i;
2384
2385 REQUIRE(VALID_DISPATCH(*dispp));
2386 disp = *dispp;
2387 *dispp = NULL;
2388
2389 mgr = disp->mgr;
2390 REQUIRE(VALID_DISPATCHMGR(mgr));
2391
2392 if (disp->tcpmsg_valid) {
2393 dns_tcpmsg_invalidate(&disp->tcpmsg);
2394 disp->tcpmsg_valid = 0;
2395 }
2396
2397 INSIST(disp->tcpbuffers == 0);
2398 INSIST(disp->requests == 0);
2399 INSIST(disp->recv_pending == 0);
2400 INSIST(ISC_LIST_EMPTY(disp->activesockets));
2401 INSIST(ISC_LIST_EMPTY(disp->inactivesockets));
2402
2403 isc_mempool_put(mgr->depool, disp->failsafe_ev);
2404 disp->failsafe_ev = NULL;
2405
2406 if (disp->qid != NULL)
2407 qid_destroy(mgr->mctx, &disp->qid);
2408
2409 if (disp->port_table != NULL) {
2410 for (i = 0; i < DNS_DISPATCH_PORTTABLESIZE; i++)
2411 INSIST(ISC_LIST_EMPTY(disp->port_table[i]));
2412 isc_mem_put(mgr->mctx, disp->port_table,
2413 sizeof(disp->port_table[0]) *
2414 DNS_DISPATCH_PORTTABLESIZE);
2415 }
2416
2417 if (disp->portpool != NULL)
2418 isc_mempool_destroy(&disp->portpool);
2419
2420 disp->mgr = NULL;
2421 isc_mutex_destroy(&disp->lock);
2422 disp->magic = 0;
2423 isc_mempool_put(mgr->dpool, disp);
2424}

2426isc_result_t
2427dns_dispatch_createtcp(dns_dispatchmgr_t *mgr, isc_socket_t *sock,
2428 isc_taskmgr_t *taskmgr, const isc_sockaddr_t *localaddr,
2429 const isc_sockaddr_t *destaddr, unsigned int buffersize,
2430 unsigned int maxbuffers, unsigned int maxrequests,
2431 unsigned int buckets, unsigned int increment,
2432 unsigned int attributes, dns_dispatch_t **dispp)
2433{
2434 isc_result_t result;
2435 dns_dispatch_t *disp;
2436
2437 UNUSED(maxbuffers);
2438 UNUSED(buffersize);
2439
2440 REQUIRE(VALID_DISPATCHMGR(mgr));
2441 REQUIRE(isc_socket_gettype(sock) == isc_sockettype_tcp);
2442 REQUIRE((attributes & DNS_DISPATCHATTR_TCP) != 0);
2443 REQUIRE((attributes & DNS_DISPATCHATTR_UDP) == 0);
2444
2445 if (destaddr == NULL)
2446 attributes |= DNS_DISPATCHATTR_PRIVATE; /* XXXMLG */
2447
2448 LOCK(&mgr->lock);
2449
2450 /*
2451 * dispatch_allocate() checks mgr for us.
2452 * qid_allocate() checks buckets and increment for us.
2453 */
2454 disp = NULL;
2455 result = dispatch_allocate(mgr, maxrequests, &disp);
2456 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2457 UNLOCK(&mgr->lock);
2458 return (result);
2459 }
2460
2461 result = qid_allocate(mgr, buckets, increment, &disp->qid, false);
2462 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
2463 goto deallocate_dispatch;
2464
2465 disp->socktype = isc_sockettype_tcp;
2466 disp->socket = NULL;
2467 isc_socket_attach(sock, &disp->socket);
2468
2469 disp->sepool = NULL;
2470
2471 disp->ntasks = 1;
2472 disp->task[0] = NULL;
2473 result = isc_task_create(taskmgr, 50, &disp->task[0]);
2474 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
2475 goto kill_socket;
2476
2477 disp->ctlevent = isc_event_allocate(mgr->mctx, disp,
2478 DNS_EVENT_DISPATCHCONTROL,
2479 destroy_disp, disp,
2480 sizeof(isc_event_t));
2481 if (disp->ctlevent == NULL) {
2482 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
2483 goto kill_task;
2484 }
2485
2486 isc_task_setname(disp->task[0], "tcpdispatch", disp);
2487
2488 dns_tcpmsg_init(mgr->mctx, disp->socket, &disp->tcpmsg);
2489 disp->tcpmsg_valid = 1;
2490
2491 disp->attributes = attributes;
2492
2493 if (localaddr == NULL) {
2494 if (destaddr != NULL) {
2495 switch (isc_sockaddr_pf(destaddr)) {
2496 case AF_INET:
2497 isc_sockaddr_any(&disp->local);
2498 break;
2499 case AF_INET6:
2500 isc_sockaddr_any6(&disp->local);
2501 break;
2502 }
2503 }
2504 } else
2505 disp->local = *localaddr;
2506
2507 if (destaddr != NULL)
2508 disp->peer = *destaddr;
2509
2510 /*
2511 * Append it to the dispatcher list.
2512 */
2513 ISC_LIST_APPEND(mgr->list, disp, link);
2514 UNLOCK(&mgr->lock);
2515
2516 mgr_log(mgr, LVL(90), "created TCP dispatcher %p", disp);
2517 dispatch_log(disp, LVL(90), "created task %p", disp->task[0]);
2518 *dispp = disp;
2519
2520 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
2521
2522 /*
2523 * Error returns.
2524 */
2525 kill_task:
2526 isc_task_detach(&disp->task[0]);
2527 kill_socket:
2528 isc_socket_detach(&disp->socket);
2529 deallocate_dispatch:
2530 dispatch_free(&disp);
2531
2532 UNLOCK(&mgr->lock);
2533
2534 return (result);
2535}

2537isc_result_t
2538dns_dispatch_gettcp(dns_dispatchmgr_t *mgr, const isc_sockaddr_t *destaddr,
2539 const isc_sockaddr_t *localaddr, bool *connected,
2540 dns_dispatch_t **dispp)
2541{
2542 dns_dispatch_t *disp;
2543 isc_result_t result;
2544 isc_sockaddr_t peeraddr;
2545 isc_sockaddr_t sockname;
2546 unsigned int attributes, mask;
2547 bool match = false;
2548
2549 REQUIRE(VALID_DISPATCHMGR(mgr));
2550 REQUIRE(destaddr != NULL);
2551 REQUIRE(dispp != NULL && *dispp == NULL);
2552
2553 /* First pass */
2554 attributes = DNS_DISPATCHATTR_TCP | DNS_DISPATCHATTR_CONNECTED;
2555 mask = DNS_DISPATCHATTR_TCP | DNS_DISPATCHATTR_PRIVATE |
2556 DNS_DISPATCHATTR_EXCLUSIVE | DNS_DISPATCHATTR_CONNECTED;
2557
2558 LOCK(&mgr->lock);
2559 disp = ISC_LIST_HEAD(mgr->list);
2560 while (disp != NULL && !match) {
2561 LOCK(&disp->lock);
2562 if ((disp->shutting_down == 0) &&
2563 ATTRMATCH(disp->attributes, attributes, mask) &&
2564 (localaddr == NULL ||
2565 isc_sockaddr_eqaddr(localaddr, &disp->local))) {
2566 result = isc_socket_getsockname(disp->socket,
2567 &sockname);
2568 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
2569 result = isc_socket_getpeername(disp->socket,
2570 &peeraddr);
2571 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS &&
2572 isc_sockaddr_equal(destaddr, &peeraddr) &&
2573 (localaddr == NULL ||
2574 isc_sockaddr_eqaddr(localaddr, &sockname))) {
2575 /* attach */
2576 disp->refcount++;
2577 *dispp = disp;
2578 match = true;
2579 if (connected != NULL) {
2580 *connected = true;
2581 }
2582 }
2583 }
2584 UNLOCK(&disp->lock);
2585 disp = ISC_LIST_NEXT(disp, link);
2586 }
2587 if (match || connected == NULL) {
2588 UNLOCK(&mgr->lock);
2589 return (match ? ISC_R_SUCCESS : ISC_R_NOTFOUND);
2590 }
2591
2592 /* Second pass, only if connected != NULL */
2593 attributes = DNS_DISPATCHATTR_TCP;
2594
2595 disp = ISC_LIST_HEAD(mgr->list);
2596 while (disp != NULL && !match) {
2597 LOCK(&disp->lock);
2598 if ((disp->shutting_down == 0) &&
2599 ATTRMATCH(disp->attributes, attributes, mask) &&
2600 (localaddr == NULL ||
2601 isc_sockaddr_eqaddr(localaddr, &disp->local)) &&
2602 isc_sockaddr_equal(destaddr, &disp->peer)) {
2603 /* attach */
2604 disp->refcount++;
2605 *dispp = disp;
2606 match = true;
2607 }
2608 UNLOCK(&disp->lock);
2609 disp = ISC_LIST_NEXT(disp, link);
2610 }
2611 UNLOCK(&mgr->lock);
2612 return (match ? ISC_R_SUCCESS : ISC_R_NOTFOUND);
2613}

2615isc_result_t
2616dns_dispatch_getudp_dup(dns_dispatchmgr_t *mgr, isc_socketmgr_t *sockmgr,
2617 isc_taskmgr_t *taskmgr, const isc_sockaddr_t *localaddr,
2618 unsigned int buffersize,
2619 unsigned int maxbuffers, unsigned int maxrequests,
2620 unsigned int buckets, unsigned int increment,
2621 unsigned int attributes, unsigned int mask,
2622 dns_dispatch_t **dispp, dns_dispatch_t *dup_dispatch)
2623{
2624 isc_result_t result;
2625 dns_dispatch_t *disp = NULL;
2626
2627 REQUIRE(VALID_DISPATCHMGR(mgr));
2628 REQUIRE(sockmgr != NULL);
2629 REQUIRE(localaddr != NULL);
2630 REQUIRE(taskmgr != NULL);
2631 REQUIRE(buffersize >= 512 && buffersize < (64 * 1024));
2632 REQUIRE(maxbuffers > 0);
2633 REQUIRE(buckets < 2097169); /* next prime > 65536 * 32 */
2634 REQUIRE(increment > buckets);
2635 REQUIRE(dispp != NULL && *dispp == NULL);
2636 REQUIRE((attributes & DNS_DISPATCHATTR_TCP) == 0);
2637
2638 result = dns_dispatchmgr_setudp(mgr, buffersize, maxbuffers,
2639 maxrequests, buckets, increment);
2640 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
2641 return (result);
2642
2643 LOCK(&mgr->lock);
2644
2645 if ((attributes & DNS_DISPATCHATTR_EXCLUSIVE) != 0) {
2646 REQUIRE(isc_sockaddr_getport(localaddr) == 0);
2647 goto createudp;
2648 }
2649
2650 /*
2651 * See if we have a dispatcher that matches.
2652 */
2653 if (dup_dispatch == NULL) {
2654 result = dispatch_find(mgr, localaddr, attributes, mask, &disp);
2655 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2656 disp->refcount++;
2657
2658 if (disp->maxrequests < maxrequests)
2659 disp->maxrequests = maxrequests;
2660
2661 if ((disp->attributes & DNS_DISPATCHATTR_NOLISTEN) == 0
2662 && (attributes & DNS_DISPATCHATTR_NOLISTEN) != 0)
2663 {
2664 disp->attributes |= DNS_DISPATCHATTR_NOLISTEN;
2665 if (disp->recv_pending != 0)
2666 isc_socket_cancel(disp->socket,
2667 disp->task[0],
2668 ISC_SOCKCANCEL_RECV);
2669 }
2670
2671 UNLOCK(&disp->lock);
2672 UNLOCK(&mgr->lock);
2673
2674 *dispp = disp;
2675
2676 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
2677 }
2678 }
2679
2680 createudp:
2681 /*
2682 * Nope, create one.
2683 */
2684 result = dispatch_createudp(mgr, sockmgr, taskmgr, localaddr,
2685 maxrequests, attributes, &disp,
2686 dup_dispatch == NULL
2687 ? NULL
2688 : dup_dispatch->socket);
2689
2690 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2691 UNLOCK(&mgr->lock);
2692 return (result);
2693 }
2694
2695 UNLOCK(&mgr->lock);
2696 *dispp = disp;
2697
2698 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
2699}

2702dns_dispatch_getudp(dns_dispatchmgr_t *mgr, isc_socketmgr_t *sockmgr,

2712 buckets, increment, attributes,
2713 mask, dispp, NULL));
2714}

2717 * mgr should be locked.
2718 */

2720#ifndef DNS_DISPATCH_HELD
2721#define DNS_DISPATCH_HELD 20U
2722#endif
2723
2724static isc_result_t
2725get_udpsocket(dns_dispatchmgr_t *mgr, dns_dispatch_t *disp,
2726 isc_socketmgr_t *sockmgr, const isc_sockaddr_t *localaddr,
2727 isc_socket_t **sockp, isc_socket_t *dup_socket, bool duponly)
2728{
2729 unsigned int i, j;
2730 isc_socket_t *held[DNS_DISPATCH_HELD];
2731 isc_sockaddr_t localaddr_bound;
2732 isc_socket_t *sock = NULL;
2733 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
2734 bool anyport;
2735
2736 INSIST(sockp != NULL && *sockp == NULL);
2737
2738 localaddr_bound = *localaddr;
2739 anyport = (isc_sockaddr_getport(localaddr) == 0);
2740
2741 if (anyport) {
2742 unsigned int nports;
2743 in_port_t *ports;
2744
2745 /*
2746 * If no port is specified, we first try to pick up a random
2747 * port by ourselves.
2748 */
2749 if (isc_sockaddr_pf(localaddr) == AF_INET) {
2750 nports = disp->mgr->nv4ports;
2751 ports = disp->mgr->v4ports;
2752 } else {
2753 nports = disp->mgr->nv6ports;
2754 ports = disp->mgr->v6ports;
2755 }
2756 if (nports == 0)
2757 return (ISC_R_ADDRNOTAVAIL);
2758
2759 for (i = 0; i < 1024; i++) {
2760 in_port_t prt;
2761
2762 prt = ports[isc_random_uniform(nports)];
2763 isc_sockaddr_setport(&localaddr_bound, prt);
2764 result = open_socket(sockmgr, &localaddr_bound,
2765 0, &sock, NULL, false);
2766 /*
2767 * Continue if the port choosen is already in use
2768 * or the OS has reserved it.
2769 */
2770 if (result == ISC_R_NOPERM ||
2771 result == ISC_R_ADDRINUSE)
2772 continue;
2773 disp->localport = prt;
2774 *sockp = sock;
2775 return (result);
2776 }
2777
2778 /*
2779 * If this fails 1024 times, we then ask the kernel for
2780 * choosing one.
2781 */
2782 } else {
2783 /* Allow to reuse address for non-random ports. */
2784 result = open_socket(sockmgr, localaddr,
2785 ISC_SOCKET_REUSEADDRESS, &sock,
2786 dup_socket, duponly);
2787
2788 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
2789 *sockp = sock;
2790
2791 return (result);
2792 }
2793
2794 memset(held, 0, sizeof(held));
2795 i = 0;
2796
2797 for (j = 0; j < 0xffffU; j++) {
2798 result = open_socket(sockmgr, localaddr, 0, &sock, NULL, false);
2799 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
2800 goto end;
2801 else if (portavailable(mgr, sock, NULL))
2802 break;
2803 if (held[i] != NULL)
2804 isc_socket_detach(&held[i]);
2805 held[i++] = sock;
2806 sock = NULL;
2807 if (i == DNS_DISPATCH_HELD)
2808 i = 0;
2809 }
2810 if (j == 0xffffU) {
2811 mgr_log(mgr, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
2812 "avoid-v%s-udp-ports: unable to allocate "
2813 "an available port",
2814 isc_sockaddr_pf(localaddr) == AF_INET ? "4" : "6");
2815 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
2816 goto end;
2817 }
2818 *sockp = sock;
2819
2820end:
2821 for (i = 0; i < DNS_DISPATCH_HELD; i++) {
2822 if (held[i] != NULL)
2823 isc_socket_detach(&held[i]);
2824 }
2825
2826 return (result);
2827}
2828
2829static isc_result_t
2830dispatch_createudp(dns_dispatchmgr_t *mgr, isc_socketmgr_t *sockmgr,
2831 isc_taskmgr_t *taskmgr,
2832 const isc_sockaddr_t *localaddr,
2833 unsigned int maxrequests,
2834 unsigned int attributes,
2835 dns_dispatch_t **dispp,
2836 isc_socket_t *dup_socket)
2837{
2838 isc_result_t result;
2839 dns_dispatch_t *disp;
2840 isc_socket_t *sock = NULL;
2841 int i = 0;
2842 bool duponly = ((attributes & DNS_DISPATCHATTR_CANREUSE) == 0);
2843
2844 /* This is an attribute needed only at creation time */
2845 attributes &= ~DNS_DISPATCHATTR_CANREUSE;
2846 /*
2847 * dispatch_allocate() checks mgr for us.
2848 */
2849 disp = NULL;
2850 result = dispatch_allocate(mgr, maxrequests, &disp);
2851 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2852 return (result);
2853 }
2854
2855 disp->socktype = isc_sockettype_udp;
2856
2857 if ((attributes & DNS_DISPATCHATTR_EXCLUSIVE) == 0) {
2858 result = get_udpsocket(mgr, disp, sockmgr, localaddr, &sock,
2859 dup_socket, duponly);
2860 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2861 goto deallocate_dispatch;
2862 }
2863
2864 if (isc_log_wouldlog(dns_lctx, 90)) {
2865 char addrbuf[ISC_SOCKADDR_FORMATSIZE];
2866
2867 isc_sockaddr_format(localaddr, addrbuf,
2868 ISC_SOCKADDR_FORMATSIZE);
2869 mgr_log(mgr, LVL(90), "dns_dispatch_createudp: Created"
2870 " UDP dispatch for %s with socket fd %d",
2871 addrbuf, isc_socket_getfd(sock));
2872 }
2873
2874 } else {
2875 isc_sockaddr_t sa_any;
2876
2877 /*
2878 * For dispatches using exclusive sockets with a specific
2879 * source address, we only check if the specified address is
2880 * available on the system. Query sockets will be created later
2881 * on demand.
2882 */
2883 isc_sockaddr_anyofpf(&sa_any, isc_sockaddr_pf(localaddr));
2884 if (!isc_sockaddr_eqaddr(&sa_any, localaddr)) {
2885 result = open_socket(sockmgr, localaddr, 0,
2886 &sock, NULL, false);
2887 if (sock != NULL) {
2888 isc_socket_detach(&sock);
2889 }
2890 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2891 goto deallocate_dispatch;
2892 }
2893 }
2894
2895 disp->port_table = isc_mem_get(mgr->mctx,
2896 sizeof(disp->port_table[0]) *
2897 DNS_DISPATCH_PORTTABLESIZE);
2898 if (disp->port_table == NULL) {
2899 goto deallocate_dispatch;
2900 }
2901 for (i = 0; i < DNS_DISPATCH_PORTTABLESIZE; i++) {
2902 ISC_LIST_INIT(disp->port_table[i]);
2903 }
2904
2905 result = isc_mempool_create(mgr->mctx, sizeof(dispportentry_t),
2906 &disp->portpool);
2907 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2908 goto deallocate_dispatch;
2909 }
2910 isc_mempool_setname(disp->portpool, "disp_portpool");
2911 isc_mempool_setfreemax(disp->portpool, 128);
2912 }
2913 disp->socket = sock;
2914 disp->local = *localaddr;
2915
2916 if ((attributes & DNS_DISPATCHATTR_EXCLUSIVE) != 0) {
2917 disp->ntasks = MAX_INTERNAL_TASKS;
2918 } else {
2919 disp->ntasks = 1;
2920 }
2921 for (i = 0; i < disp->ntasks; i++) {
2922 disp->task[i] = NULL;
2923 result = isc_task_create(taskmgr, 0, &disp->task[i]);
2924 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2925 while (--i >= 0) {
2926 isc_task_shutdown(disp->task[i]);
2927 isc_task_detach(&disp->task[i]);
2928 }
2929 goto kill_socket;
2930 }
2931 isc_task_setname(disp->task[i], "udpdispatch", disp);
2932 }
2933
2934 disp->ctlevent = isc_event_allocate(mgr->mctx, disp,
2935 DNS_EVENT_DISPATCHCONTROL,
2936 destroy_disp, disp,
2937 sizeof(isc_event_t));
2938 if (disp->ctlevent == NULL) {
2939 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
2940 goto kill_task;
2941 }
2942
2943 disp->sepool = NULL;
2944 if (isc_mempool_create(mgr->mctx, sizeof(isc_socketevent_t),
2945 &disp->sepool) != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
2946 {
2947 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
2948 goto kill_ctlevent;
2949 }
2950
2951 isc_mutex_init(&disp->sepool_lock);
2952
2953 isc_mempool_setname(disp->sepool, "disp_sepool");
2954 isc_mempool_setmaxalloc(disp->sepool, 32768);
2955 isc_mempool_setfreemax(disp->sepool, 32768);
2956 isc_mempool_associatelock(disp->sepool, &disp->sepool_lock);
2957 isc_mempool_setfillcount(disp->sepool, 16);
2958
2959 attributes &= ~DNS_DISPATCHATTR_TCP;
2960 attributes |= DNS_DISPATCHATTR_UDP;
2961 disp->attributes = attributes;
2962
2963 /*
2964 * Append it to the dispatcher list.
2965 */
2966 ISC_LIST_APPEND(mgr->list, disp, link);
2967
2968 mgr_log(mgr, LVL(90), "created UDP dispatcher %p", disp);
2969 dispatch_log(disp, LVL(90), "created task %p", disp->task[0]); /* XXX */
2970 if (disp->socket != NULL) {
2971 dispatch_log(disp, LVL(90), "created socket %p", disp->socket);
2972 }
2973
2974 *dispp = disp;
2975
2976 return (result);
2977
2978 /*
2979 * Error returns.
2980 */
2981 kill_ctlevent:
2982 isc_event_free(&disp->ctlevent);
2983 kill_task:
2984 for (i = 0; i < disp->ntasks; i++) {
2985 isc_task_detach(&disp->task[i]);
2986 }
2987 kill_socket:
2988 if (disp->socket != NULL) {
2989 isc_socket_detach(&disp->socket);
2990 }
2991 deallocate_dispatch:
2992 dispatch_free(&disp);
2993
2994 return (result);
2995}

2997void
2998dns_dispatch_attach(dns_dispatch_t *disp, dns_dispatch_t **dispp) {
2999 REQUIRE(VALID_DISPATCH(disp));
3000 REQUIRE(dispp != NULL && *dispp == NULL);
3001
3002 LOCK(&disp->lock);
3003 disp->refcount++;
3004 UNLOCK(&disp->lock);
3005
3006 *dispp = disp;
3007}
3008
3009/*
3010 * It is important to lock the manager while we are deleting the dispatch,
3011 * since dns_dispatch_getudp will call dispatch_find, which returns to
3012 * the caller a dispatch but does not attach to it until later. _getudp
3013 * locks the manager, however, so locking it here will keep us from attaching
3014 * to a dispatcher that is in the process of going away.
3015 */
3016void
3017dns_dispatch_detach(dns_dispatch_t **dispp) {
3018 dns_dispatch_t *disp;
3019 dispsocket_t *dispsock;
3020 bool killit;
3021
3022 REQUIRE(dispp != NULL && VALID_DISPATCH(*dispp));
3023
3024 disp = *dispp;
3025 *dispp = NULL;
3026
3027 LOCK(&disp->lock);
3028
3029 INSIST(disp->refcount > 0);
3030 disp->refcount--;
3031 if (disp->refcount == 0) {
3032 if (disp->recv_pending > 0)
3033 isc_socket_cancel(disp->socket, disp->task[0],
3034 ISC_SOCKCANCEL_RECV);
3035 for (dispsock = ISC_LIST_HEAD(disp->activesockets);
3036 dispsock != NULL;
3037 dispsock = ISC_LIST_NEXT(dispsock, link)) {
3038 isc_socket_cancel(dispsock->socket, dispsock->task,
3039 ISC_SOCKCANCEL_RECV);
3040 }
3041 disp->shutting_down = 1;
3042 }
3043
3044 dispatch_log(disp, LVL(90), "detach: refcount %d", disp->refcount);
3045
3046 killit = destroy_disp_ok(disp);
3047 UNLOCK(&disp->lock);
3048 if (killit)
3049 isc_task_send(disp->task[0], &disp->ctlevent);
3050}
