3052isc_result_t
3053dns_dispatch_addresponse(dns_dispatch_t *disp, unsigned int options,
3054 const isc_sockaddr_t *dest, isc_task_t *task,
3055 isc_taskaction_t action, void *arg,
3056 dns_messageid_t *idp, dns_dispentry_t **resp,
3057 isc_socketmgr_t *sockmgr)
3058{
3059 dns_dispentry_t *res;
3060 unsigned int bucket;
3061 in_port_t localport = 0;
3062 dns_messageid_t id;
3063 int i;
3064 bool ok;
3065 dns_qid_t *qid;
3066 dispsocket_t *dispsocket = NULL;
3067 isc_result_t result;
3068
3069 REQUIRE(VALID_DISPATCH(disp));
3070 REQUIRE(task != NULL);
3071 REQUIRE(dest != NULL);
3072 REQUIRE(resp != NULL && *resp == NULL);
3073 REQUIRE(idp != NULL);
3074 if ((disp->attributes & DNS_DISPATCHATTR_EXCLUSIVE) != 0)
3075 REQUIRE(sockmgr != NULL);
3076
3077 LOCK(&disp->lock);
3078
3079 if (disp->shutting_down == 1) {
3080 UNLOCK(&disp->lock);
3081 return (ISC_R_SHUTTINGDOWN);
3082 }
3083
3084 if (disp->requests >= disp->maxrequests) {
3085 UNLOCK(&disp->lock);
3086 return (ISC_R_QUOTA);
3087 }
3088
3089 if ((disp->attributes & DNS_DISPATCHATTR_EXCLUSIVE) != 0 &&
3090 disp->nsockets > DNS_DISPATCH_SOCKSQUOTA) {
3091 dispsocket_t *oldestsocket;
3092 dns_dispentry_t *oldestresp;
3093 dns_dispatchevent_t *rev;
3094
3095 /*
3096 * Kill oldest outstanding query if the number of sockets
3097 * exceeds the quota to keep the room for new queries.
3098 */
3099 oldestsocket = ISC_LIST_HEAD(disp->activesockets);
3100 oldestresp = oldestsocket->resp;
3101 if (oldestresp != NULL && !oldestresp->item_out) {
3102 rev = allocate_devent(oldestresp->disp);
3103 if (rev != NULL) {
3104 rev->buffer.base = NULL;
3105 rev->result = ISC_R_CANCELED;
3106 rev->id = oldestresp->id;
3107 ISC_EVENT_INIT(rev, sizeof(*rev), 0,
3108 NULL, DNS_EVENT_DISPATCH,
3109 oldestresp->action,
3110 oldestresp->arg, oldestresp,
3111 NULL, NULL);
3112 oldestresp->item_out = true;
3113 isc_task_send(oldestresp->task,
3114 ISC_EVENT_PTR(&rev));
3115 inc_stats(disp->mgr,
3116 dns_resstatscounter_dispabort);
3117 }
3118 }
3119
3120 /*
3121 * Move this entry to the tail so that it won't (easily) be
3122 * examined before actually being canceled.
3123 */
3124 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(disp->activesockets, oldestsocket, link);
3125 ISC_LIST_APPEND(disp->activesockets, oldestsocket, link);
3126 }
3127
3128 qid = DNS_QID(disp);
3129
3130 if ((disp->attributes & DNS_DISPATCHATTR_EXCLUSIVE) != 0) {
3131 /*
3132 * Get a separate UDP socket with a random port number.
3133 */
3134 result = get_dispsocket(disp, dest, sockmgr, &dispsocket,
3135 &localport);
3136 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
3137 UNLOCK(&disp->lock);
3138 inc_stats(disp->mgr, dns_resstatscounter_dispsockfail);
3139 return (result);
3140 }
3141 } else {
3142 localport = disp->localport;
3143 }
3144
3145 /*
3146 * Try somewhat hard to find an unique ID unless FIXEDID is set
3147 * in which case we use the id passed in via *idp.
3148 */
3149 LOCK(&qid->lock);
3150 if ((options & DNS_DISPATCHOPT_FIXEDID) != 0) {
3151 id = *idp;
3152 } else {
3153 id = (dns_messageid_t)isc_random16();
3154 }
3155 ok = false;
3156 i = 0;
3157 do {
3158 bucket = dns_hash(qid, dest, id, localport);
3159 if (entry_search(qid, dest, id, localport, bucket) == NULL) {
3160 ok = true;
3161 break;
3162 }
3163 if ((disp->attributes & DNS_DISPATCHATTR_FIXEDID) != 0)
3164 break;
3165 id += qid->qid_increment;
3166 id &= 0x0000ffff;
3167 } while (i++ < 64);
3168 UNLOCK(&qid->lock);
3169
3170 if (!ok) {
3171 UNLOCK(&disp->lock);
3172 return (ISC_R_NOMORE);
3173 }
3174
3175 res = isc_mempool_get(disp->mgr->rpool);
3176 if (res == NULL) {
3177 if (dispsocket != NULL)
3178 destroy_dispsocket(disp, &dispsocket);
3179 UNLOCK(&disp->lock);
3180 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
3181 }
3182
3183 disp->refcount++;
3184 disp->requests++;
3185 res->task = NULL;
3186 isc_task_attach(task, &res->task);
3187 res->disp = disp;
3188 res->id = id;
3189 res->port = localport;
3190 res->bucket = bucket;
3191 res->host = *dest;
3192 res->action = action;
3193 res->arg = arg;
3194 res->dispsocket = dispsocket;
3195 if (dispsocket != NULL)
3196 dispsocket->resp = res;
3197 res->item_out = false;
3198 ISC_LIST_INIT(res->items);
3199 ISC_LINK_INIT(res, link);
3200 res->magic = RESPONSE_MAGIC;
3201
3202 LOCK(&qid->lock);
3203 ISC_LIST_APPEND(qid->qid_table[bucket], res, link);
3204 UNLOCK(&qid->lock);
3205
3206 inc_stats(disp->mgr, (qid == disp->mgr->qid) ?
3207 dns_resstatscounter_disprequdp :
3208 dns_resstatscounter_dispreqtcp);
3209
3210 request_log(disp, res, LVL(90),
3211 "attached to task %p", res->task);
3212
3213 if (((disp->attributes & DNS_DISPATCHATTR_UDP) != 0) ||
3214 ((disp->attributes & DNS_DISPATCHATTR_CONNECTED) != 0)) {
3215 result = startrecv(disp, dispsocket);
3216 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
3217 LOCK(&qid->lock);
3218 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(qid->qid_table[bucket], res, link);
3219 UNLOCK(&qid->lock);
3220
3221 if (dispsocket != NULL)
3222 destroy_dispsocket(disp, &dispsocket);
3223
3224 disp->refcount--;
3225 disp->requests--;
3226
3227 dec_stats(disp->mgr, (qid == disp->mgr->qid) ?
3228 dns_resstatscounter_disprequdp :
3229 dns_resstatscounter_dispreqtcp);
3230
3231 UNLOCK(&disp->lock);
3232 isc_task_detach(&res->task);
3233 isc_mempool_put(disp->mgr->rpool, res);
3234 return (result);
3235 }
3236 }
3237
3238 if (dispsocket != NULL)
3239 ISC_LIST_APPEND(disp->activesockets, dispsocket, link);
3240
3241 UNLOCK(&disp->lock);
3242
3243 *idp = id;
3244 *resp = res;
3245
3246 if ((disp->attributes & DNS_DISPATCHATTR_EXCLUSIVE) != 0)
3247 INSIST(res->dispsocket != NULL);
3248
3249 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
3250}

3309void
3310dns_dispatch_removeresponse(dns_dispentry_t **resp,
3311 dns_dispatchevent_t **sockevent)
3312{
3313 dns_dispatchmgr_t *mgr;
3314 dns_dispatch_t *disp;
3315 dns_dispentry_t *res;
3316 dispsocket_t *dispsock;
3317 dns_dispatchevent_t *ev;
3318 unsigned int bucket;
3319 bool killit;
3320 unsigned int n;
3321 isc_eventlist_t events;
3322 dns_qid_t *qid;
3323
3324 REQUIRE(resp != NULL);
3325 REQUIRE(VALID_RESPONSE(*resp));
3326
3327 res = *resp;
3328 *resp = NULL;
3329
3330 disp = res->disp;
3331 REQUIRE(VALID_DISPATCH(disp));
3332 mgr = disp->mgr;
3333 REQUIRE(VALID_DISPATCHMGR(mgr));
3334
3335 qid = DNS_QID(disp);
3336
3337 if (sockevent != NULL) {
3338 REQUIRE(*sockevent != NULL);
3339 ev = *sockevent;
3340 *sockevent = NULL;
3341 } else {
3342 ev = NULL;
3343 }
3344
3345 LOCK(&disp->lock);
3346
3347 INSIST(disp->requests > 0);
3348 disp->requests--;
3349 dec_stats(disp->mgr, (qid == disp->mgr->qid) ?
3350 dns_resstatscounter_disprequdp :
3351 dns_resstatscounter_dispreqtcp);
3352 INSIST(disp->refcount > 0);
3353 disp->refcount--;
3354 if (disp->refcount == 0) {
3355 if (disp->recv_pending > 0)
3356 isc_socket_cancel(disp->socket, disp->task[0],
3357 ISC_SOCKCANCEL_RECV);
3358 for (dispsock = ISC_LIST_HEAD(disp->activesockets);
3359 dispsock != NULL;
3360 dispsock = ISC_LIST_NEXT(dispsock, link)) {
3361 isc_socket_cancel(dispsock->socket, dispsock->task,
3362 ISC_SOCKCANCEL_RECV);
3363 }
3364 disp->shutting_down = 1;
3365 }
3366
3367 bucket = res->bucket;
3368
3369 LOCK(&qid->lock);
3370 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(qid->qid_table[bucket], res, link);
3371 UNLOCK(&qid->lock);
3372
3373 if (ev == NULL && res->item_out) {
3374 /*
3375 * We've posted our event, but the caller hasn't gotten it
3376 * yet. Take it back.
3377 */
3378 ISC_LIST_INIT(events);
3379 n = isc_task_unsend(res->task, res, DNS_EVENT_DISPATCH,
3380 NULL, &events);
3381 /*
3382 * We had better have gotten it back.
3383 */
3384 INSIST(n == 1);
3385 ev = (dns_dispatchevent_t *)ISC_LIST_HEAD(events);
3386 }
3387
3388 if (ev != NULL) {
3389 REQUIRE(res->item_out == true);
3390 res->item_out = false;
3391 if (ev->buffer.base != NULL)
3392 free_buffer(disp, ev->buffer.base, ev->buffer.length);
3393 free_devent(disp, ev);
3394 }
3395
3396 request_log(disp, res, LVL(90), "detaching from task %p", res->task);
3397 isc_task_detach(&res->task);
3398
3399 if (res->dispsocket != NULL) {
3400 isc_socket_cancel(res->dispsocket->socket,
3401 res->dispsocket->task, ISC_SOCKCANCEL_RECV);
3402 res->dispsocket->resp = NULL;
3403 }
3404
3405 /*
3406 * Free any buffered responses as well
3407 */
3408 ev = ISC_LIST_HEAD(res->items);
3409 while (ev != NULL) {
3410 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(res->items, ev, ev_link);
3411 if (ev->buffer.base != NULL)
3412 free_buffer(disp, ev->buffer.base, ev->buffer.length);
3413 free_devent(disp, ev);
3414 ev = ISC_LIST_HEAD(res->items);
3415 }
3416 res->magic = 0;
3417 isc_mempool_put(disp->mgr->rpool, res);
3418 if (disp->shutting_down == 1)
3419 do_cancel(disp);
3420 else
3421 (void)startrecv(disp, NULL);
3422
3423 killit = destroy_disp_ok(disp);
3424 UNLOCK(&disp->lock);
3425 if (killit)
3426 isc_task_send(disp->task[0], &disp->ctlevent);
3427}
3428
3429static void
3430do_cancel(dns_dispatch_t *disp) {
3431 dns_dispatchevent_t *ev;
3432 dns_dispentry_t *resp;
3433 dns_qid_t *qid;
3434
3435 if (disp->shutdown_out == 1)
3436 return;
3437
3438 qid = DNS_QID(disp);
3439
3440 /*
3441 * Search for the first response handler without packets outstanding
3442 * unless a specific hander is given.
3443 */
3444 LOCK(&qid->lock);
3445 for (resp = linear_first(qid);
3446 resp != NULL && resp->item_out;
3447 /* Empty. */)
3448 resp = linear_next(qid, resp);
3449
3450 /*
3451 * No one to send the cancel event to, so nothing to do.
3452 */
3453 if (resp == NULL)
3454 goto unlock;
3455
3456 /*
3457 * Send the shutdown failsafe event to this resp.
3458 */
3459 ev = disp->failsafe_ev;
3460 ISC_EVENT_INIT(ev, sizeof(*ev), 0, NULL, DNS_EVENT_DISPATCH,
3461 resp->action, resp->arg, resp, NULL, NULL);
3462 ev->result = disp->shutdown_why;
3463 ev->buffer.base = NULL;
3464 ev->buffer.length = 0;
3465 disp->shutdown_out = 1;
3466 request_log(disp, resp, LVL(10),
3467 "cancel: failsafe event %p -> task %p",
3468 ev, resp->task);
3469 resp->item_out = true;
3470 isc_task_send(resp->task, ISC_EVENT_PTR(&ev));
3471 unlock:
3472 UNLOCK(&qid->lock);
3473}

3505void
3506dns_dispatch_cancel(dns_dispatch_t *disp) {
3507 REQUIRE(VALID_DISPATCH(disp));
3508
3509 LOCK(&disp->lock);
3510
3511 if (disp->shutting_down == 1) {
3512 UNLOCK(&disp->lock);
3513 return;
3514 }
3515
3516 disp->shutdown_why = ISC_R_CANCELED;
3517 disp->shutting_down = 1;
3518 do_cancel(disp);
3519
3520 UNLOCK(&disp->lock);
3521
3522 return;
3523}

3536void
3537dns_dispatch_changeattributes(dns_dispatch_t *disp,
3538 unsigned int attributes, unsigned int mask)
3539{
3540 REQUIRE(VALID_DISPATCH(disp));
3541 /* Exclusive attribute can only be set on creation */
3542 REQUIRE((attributes & DNS_DISPATCHATTR_EXCLUSIVE) == 0);
3543 /* Also, a dispatch with randomport specified cannot start listening */
3544 REQUIRE((disp->attributes & DNS_DISPATCHATTR_EXCLUSIVE) == 0 ||
3545 (attributes & DNS_DISPATCHATTR_NOLISTEN) == 0);
3546
3547 /* XXXMLG
3548 * Should check for valid attributes here!
3549 */
3550
3551 LOCK(&disp->lock);
3552
3553 if ((mask & DNS_DISPATCHATTR_NOLISTEN) != 0) {
3554 if ((disp->attributes & DNS_DISPATCHATTR_NOLISTEN) != 0 &&
3555 (attributes & DNS_DISPATCHATTR_NOLISTEN) == 0) {
3556 disp->attributes &= ~DNS_DISPATCHATTR_NOLISTEN;
3557 (void)startrecv(disp, NULL);
3558 } else if ((disp->attributes & DNS_DISPATCHATTR_NOLISTEN)
3559 == 0 &&
3560 (attributes & DNS_DISPATCHATTR_NOLISTEN) != 0) {
3561 disp->attributes |= DNS_DISPATCHATTR_NOLISTEN;
3562 if (disp->recv_pending != 0)
3563 isc_socket_cancel(disp->socket, disp->task[0],
3564 ISC_SOCKCANCEL_RECV);
3565 }
3566 }
3567
3568 disp->attributes &= ~mask;
3569 disp->attributes |= (attributes & mask);
3570 UNLOCK(&disp->lock);
3571}

3573void
3574dns_dispatch_importrecv(dns_dispatch_t *disp, isc_event_t *event) {
3575 void *buf;
3576 isc_socketevent_t *sevent, *newsevent;
3577
3578 REQUIRE(VALID_DISPATCH(disp));
3579 REQUIRE(event != NULL);
3580
3581 if ((disp->attributes & DNS_DISPATCHATTR_NOLISTEN) == 0)
3582 return;
3583
3584 sevent = (isc_socketevent_t *)event;
3585 INSIST(sevent->n <= disp->mgr->buffersize);
3586
3587 newsevent = (isc_socketevent_t *)
3588 isc_event_allocate(disp->mgr->mctx, NULL,
3589 DNS_EVENT_IMPORTRECVDONE, udp_shrecv,
3590 disp, sizeof(isc_socketevent_t));
3591 if (newsevent == NULL)
3592 return;
3593
3594 buf = allocate_udp_buffer(disp);
3595 if (buf == NULL) {
3596 isc_event_free(ISC_EVENT_PTR(&newsevent));
3597 return;
3598 }
3599 memmove(buf, sevent->region.base, sevent->n);
3600 newsevent->region.base = buf;
3601 newsevent->region.length = disp->mgr->buffersize;
3602 newsevent->n = sevent->n;
3603 newsevent->result = sevent->result;
3604 newsevent->address = sevent->address;
3605 newsevent->timestamp = sevent->timestamp;
3606 newsevent->pktinfo = sevent->pktinfo;
3607 newsevent->attributes = sevent->attributes;
3608
3609 isc_task_send(disp->task[0], ISC_EVENT_PTR(&newsevent));
3610}

3612dns_dispatch_t *
3613dns_dispatchset_get(dns_dispatchset_t *dset) {
3614 dns_dispatch_t *disp;
3615
3616 /* check that dispatch set is configured */
3617 if (dset == NULL || dset->ndisp == 0)
3618 return (NULL);
3619
3620 LOCK(&dset->lock);
3621 disp = dset->dispatches[dset->cur];
3622 dset->cur++;
3623 if (dset->cur == dset->ndisp)
3624 dset->cur = 0;
3625 UNLOCK(&dset->lock);
3626
3627 return (disp);
3628}

3630isc_result_t
3631dns_dispatchset_create(isc_mem_t *mctx, isc_socketmgr_t *sockmgr,
3632 isc_taskmgr_t *taskmgr, dns_dispatch_t *source,
3633 dns_dispatchset_t **dsetp, int n)
3634{
3635 isc_result_t result;
3636 dns_dispatchset_t *dset;
3637 dns_dispatchmgr_t *mgr;
3638 int i, j;
3639
3640 REQUIRE(VALID_DISPATCH(source));
3641 REQUIRE((source->attributes & DNS_DISPATCHATTR_UDP) != 0);
3642 REQUIRE(dsetp != NULL && *dsetp == NULL);
3643
3644 mgr = source->mgr;
3645
3646 dset = isc_mem_get(mctx, sizeof(dns_dispatchset_t));
3647 if (dset == NULL)
3648 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
3649 memset(dset, 0, sizeof(*dset));
3650
3651 isc_mutex_init(&dset->lock);
3652
3653 dset->dispatches = isc_mem_get(mctx, sizeof(dns_dispatch_t *) * n);
3654 if (dset->dispatches == NULL) {
3655 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
3656 goto fail_lock;
3657 }
3658
3659 isc_mem_attach(mctx, &dset->mctx);
3660 dset->ndisp = n;
3661 dset->cur = 0;
3662
3663 dset->dispatches[0] = NULL;
3664 dns_dispatch_attach(source, &dset->dispatches[0]);
3665
3666 LOCK(&mgr->lock);
3667 for (i = 1; i < n; i++) {
3668 dset->dispatches[i] = NULL;
3669 result = dispatch_createudp(mgr, sockmgr, taskmgr,
3670 &source->local,
3671 source->maxrequests,
3672 source->attributes,
3673 &dset->dispatches[i],
3674 source->socket);
3675 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3676 goto fail;
3677 }
3678
3679 UNLOCK(&mgr->lock);
3680 *dsetp = dset;
3681
3682 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
3683
3684 fail:
3685 UNLOCK(&mgr->lock);
3686
3687 for (j = 0; j < i; j++)
3688 dns_dispatch_detach(&(dset->dispatches[j]));
3689 isc_mem_put(mctx, dset->dispatches, sizeof(dns_dispatch_t *) * n);
3690 if (dset->mctx == mctx)
3691 isc_mem_detach(&dset->mctx);
3692
3693 fail_lock:
3694 isc_mutex_destroy(&dset->lock);
3695 isc_mem_put(mctx, dset, sizeof(dns_dispatchset_t));
3696 return (result);
3697}

3713dns_dispatchset_destroy(dns_dispatchset_t **dsetp) {
3714 dns_dispatchset_t *dset;
3715 int i;
3716
3717 REQUIRE(dsetp != NULL && *dsetp != NULL);
3718
3719 dset = *dsetp;
3720 for (i = 0; i < dset->ndisp; i++)
3721 dns_dispatch_detach(&(dset->dispatches[i]));

3723 sizeof(dns_dispatch_t *) * dset->ndisp);
